title: bread and butter pickles
directions: You will also need sterilized canning jars.

title: cheese bites
directions: Quarter biscuits; arrange in 2 greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans.
Melt butter and cheese; stir until blended.
Drizzle over biscuits.
Bake in a 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 40.

title: old fashioned banana pudding
directions: Make a custard by combining the first 3 ingredients and adding the milk to which has been added the slightly beaten egg yolks. Cook in top of double boiler until the consistency of custard.
Add vanilla.
Line a baking dish with vanilla wafers.
Pour over this 1/4 the custard.
Repeat with another layer of wafers and bananas. Cover with remaining custard.
Make meringue of egg whites, whipped.
Add 12 tablespoons of sugar.
Beat until stiff and put on top of pudding.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, butter, vanilla and salt.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and raisins or nuts.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper on cookie sheet.
Spread mixture evenly; cut into squares.

title: cheddar balls
directions: Grease a cookie sheet.
Mix cheese, flour and butter lightly with hands.
Add water to make stiff dough; shape dough into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake another 15 minutes or until center is firm.

title: c. a.'s cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables in bouillon until tender.
Warm milk.
Add cornstarch slowly to hot milk.
Add vegetables.
Add american cheese slowly.
Stir as cheese melts.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: potato casserole(serves 20)
directions: Mix all together, then mix 1/4 cup butter and 2 cups crushed corn flakes. Sprinkle this on top of mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil, bone and skin chicken.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Saute chopped onion in a bit of margarine.
Add onion, cheese and chips to chicken.
Mix soups and Ro-Tel.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Put in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle chips on top for last 5 minutes of baking.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with vegetables of your choice.

title: pineapple cheese dip
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save juice.
Butter baking dish and make first layer with half of pineapple.

title: taffy tan fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil. Cook 5 minutes or to soft-ball stage. Remove and add marshmallow cream and peanut butter. Beat until smooth. Pour in a 9-inch square pan.

title: irish cream
directions: Put in blender and beat until mixed.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cream puffs
directions: Put margarine and water in a saucepan on high heat.
When mixture boils, add flour.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly. When mixture comes to a big ball, remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat until smooth.

title: louisiana chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients, including cocoa, together and add alternately with milk and vanilla, beginning and ending with the dry ingredients.
Grease and flour a tube cake pan.
Pour batter into pan and gently press nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cake is moist and will keep for days.
Makes about 25 servings.

title: cup salad
directions: Mix as for any congealed salad.
This is a tart salad and goes well with most meats.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve.

title: church supper casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salt water; drain.
In a large skillet, melt butter and brown meat.
Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Stir in tomato sauce, flour and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Mix together the cottage cheese, sour cream, salt, onion, green pepper and olives.
Put 1/2 noodles in casserole.
Spread on cottage cheese mixture.
Top with remaining noodles; cover with remaining ground beef mixture.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 10.

title: chocolate dip
directions: Combine cocoa, cornstarch and water in pan.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until boils.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla; stir.
Cool at room temperature.
Serve with whole strawberries.

title: coffee cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° on greased and floured cookie sheet.

title: jalapeno squares
directions: Butter oblong cake pan.
Line pan with peppers.
Top with grated cheese.
Dribble eggs over cheese.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares.

title: baked steak
directions: Use a piece of heavy duty foil large enough to completely wrap the meat.
Use a cookie sheet or oblong cake pan and put foil in bottom of pan.
Pour 1/2 of onion soup mix, mushrooms, water and wine mixture onto foil.
Place steak on top of mixture.
Pour the other half of mixture onto the top of the meat.
Wrap foil around steak securely.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: white icing
directions: Use electric mixer to make a fluffier frosting.
This type frosting is used for wedding cakes.

title: oatmeal fruited cookies
directions: Beat Crisco, sugar and eggs until fluffy; beat in vanilla. Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in fruit, nuts and chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoon onto cookie sheet that has been sprayed lightly with Pam.
Bake 13 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cool 2 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon and set aside.

title: purple stuff
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch glass rectangular dish, add boiling water to jello mixes and stir.
Add pineapple and blueberry pie filling, then chill until it has gelled.
Blend remaining ingredients and spread over the top. May be served immediately or chilled for later.

title: broccoli salad(servings:  4)
directions: Peel stems of broccoli and chop into fine pieces.
Mix vegetables and bacon together.

title: roni roni and cheese
directions: Let Mama fix Roni Roni and cheese.
Put in plate and cool for me.
Pick up Roni Roni and cheese with hand and eat.
Real good.

title: custard(the kind you drink - and warm is best!)
directions: In double boiler, with water in bottom half and milk in the top container, heat until milk is very hot.
Mix sugar with yellow of eggs and stir into hot milk.
Beat whites and after custard has cooked 15 or 20 minutes, stir in whites.
Add vanilla.
Makes about 10 cups.
Serve warm or refrigerate and serve cold.

title: chocolate raspberry sauce
directions: In a heavy saucepan, bring cream to a simmer with the jam, whisking.
Remove the pan from the heat.
Add the chocolates and a pinch of salt.
Let the mixture stand for 3 minutes.
Whisk it until it is smooth; whisk in the cassis.
Strain the sauce through a fine sieve set over a bowl; serve it warm over ice cream.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: date balls
directions: Melt brown sugar and margarine together.
Mix with dates and coconut.
Cook 6 minutes on medium heat.
Cool slightly and add pecans.
Cool.
Add Rice Krispies.
Cool and shape into balls. Again cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: oxtail soup
directions: Wash and dry oxtail pieces and roll them lightly in flour. Heat oil in a large heavy pot and when it is hot, brown the oxtail pieces.
Add the stock; stir and bring to a boil.
Cover pot with a loose fitting lid; adjust heat to simmer and cook for 2 hours. Add carrots, leeks and onion.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour more.

title: libbie's funeral bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with whole graham crackers.
Bring oleo and sugar to a boil; cook for 2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Cut.
Let cool.

title: brown rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Add consomme soup, rice, French onion soup and mushrooms (if using). Mix well, cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low calorie dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender for 30 seconds.
Pour mixture in glass container and keep refrigerated.
Shake well before each use.
This is not only good on salad, but tasty on burgers.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan as directed.
Cook together pineapple with juice and sugar for about 8 minutes.
Punch holes in cake with wooden spoon when hot.
Pour pineapple mixture over cake.
Cool.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together. Pour in 9-inch pie pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: japanese potato salad
directions: Peel and boil potatoes.
Boil eggs.
Mix and mash potatoes and eggs.
Shred cucumber.
Add cucumber, mayonnaise, sugar and crab meat.
Mix well.
Top with cucumber or anything you desire. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheesy carrots
directions: Pare and slice carrots into rounds.
Boil carrots and onion until tender; drain.
Put into greased 11 x 14-inch pan.
Shred Velveeta or cut into small chunks.
Put cheese and slices of margarine over vegetables.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: homemade cherry ice cream
directions: Puree cherries in blender.
Combine sugar, sweetened milk, half and half and vanilla and pour into 6 qt. ice cream freezer. Fill to "fill line" with whole milk.
Freeze according to freezer directions

title: hobo hash
directions: You will need one small pumpkin.
Wash and ream out seeds and pulp.
Sprinkle inside with salt and pepper.
Fill pumpkin with your favorite meat loaf recipe.
Place in a shallow pan with water in it.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Pumpkin will be soft. Serve in quarters.

title: baked rice
directions: Brown vermicelli in oil.
Brown rice in margarine.
Add consomme, water and bouillon cube.
Salt and pepper.
Put in casserole.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 350°.
Serve with meat of your choice.

title: baked apple slices
directions: Peel and slice the apples in quarters.
Place in flat Pyrex pan.
Boil the water, margarine and cinnamon for about 2 minutes. Pour over apples. Bake about 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender, except poppy seed.
Blend 30 seconds.
Scrape sides.
Stir in poppy seed.

title: chicken veggie casserole
directions: Place chicken in a greased shallow 2 qt. baking dish. Top with carrots, potatoes and celery. Combine the soup, water, salt, and pepper, pour over the vegetables.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on box.
Prepare shells as directed.
Mix soup and water in bowl.
Pour enough soup mixture into bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish to cover.
Set aside.
Mix chicken, stuffing and mayonnaise.
Stuff each shell with mixture and place in baking dish.
Pour remaining soup over shells. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: french corn bread
directions: Cook in hot oven at 450°.
One big difference in this type of bread is you can warm this bread over and it is still delicious. Hope you enjoy it.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, salt and milk.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water when tested.
Remove from fire and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Immediately pour over nuts, working until crystallized.

title: budget punch
directions: Combine sugar, 14 cups lukewarm water and 5 tablespoons citric acid in a large dishpan.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Now add vanilla, juice and 10 quarts of water.
Use food coloring to make punch your choice when a little is poured in a glass.
Chill until ready to use, then add ginger ale and stir.
I sometimes freeze a small bowl full and add to punch bowl before serving.

title: working mom brisket
directions: Sprinkle both sides of frozen brisket with the garlic salt. Place in turkey-sized baking bag.
Place in open roast pan.
Prick top of bag 4 or 5 times.
Before you go to bed, place in a 250° oven.
Next morning, remove and trim.
Refrigerate until supper time.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients until they liquify. Chill before serving.

title: creamed corn
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 5 minutes.
Blend 2 tablespoons melted butter and 2 tablespoons flour.
Add to corn.
Mix well.
Remove from heat.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Remove skin from salmon and flake.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Turn into a greased or oiled 7 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan and bake in a moderately hot oven of 375° for 40 minutes or until firm in center.
Serve with 1 cup medium white sauce in the making of which the reserved salmon liquid has been used as part of the milk.
Before serving sauce, stir in 2 tablespoons of ketchup.
Serves 4.

title: waneta's corn salad
directions: Rinse peas, but do not cook.
Drain all vegetables.
Mix and allow to marinate overnight.

title: pie dough #2
directions: Blend well with oil mixture.
Pat into pie pan (do not roll out).
For cream pies, pierce dough on bottom. Bake 5 to 10 minutes, depending on how done you want it at 325° to 350°.

title: wonderful strawberry pie
directions: Line pie shell with strawberries.
Combine remaining ingredients in a sauce pan and blend in 1 cup of water.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes or until it is thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Spoon over strawberries and chill until ready to serve.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: In bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in milk, lemon juice and food coloring, if desired.
Pour in crust.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add pieces of bananas and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Cover top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: foley's fashnachts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and add 4 teaspoons sugar.
In another saucepan, put warm milk and 3 cups flour; add yeast and let raise.
In yet another saucepan, put 2 cups milk, 2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup Crisco, 1/2 cup butter and 2 teaspoons salt.
Dissolve until lukewarm and add the eggs.
Add this to yeast mix, which has become spongy.
Add, slowly, the remaining 5 pounds flour.
Let raise until double its size (takes about 1 hour).
Roll out and cut out center and cut into small squares.
Let rise again (about 1 hour). Fry in about 3 pounds Crisco until golden brown.

title: quick and easy sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix
biscuit mix and sausage until
well
blended.
Add grated cheese and mix.
Form into walnut size balls and place on a paper plate.
It works best to use a circular arrangement for
best results
and more even cooking.
Microwave about 20 balls
at
a time on High.
Let stand 1 minute, then test for doneness.
Cook 1
minute
longer, if needed.
Makes about 60 walnut size balls.

title: super simple soup
directions: Prepare noodles as directed; drain.
In large kettle, cook broth, sausage, cabbage, carrots and green onions just until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in macaroni and heat through.
Ready to serve. Serves 6.

title: aunt louise's white sauce(banana pudding)
directions: Scald
milk.
Mix dry ingredients, stirring constantly. Add milk.
Cook
until it thickens.
Beat egg yolks slightly; add some hot
mixture.
Add
to
pan
and cook 3 to 4 minutes longer. Cool
slightly and then add butter and vanilla.
Cool completely.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Mixing after each, add eggs, sweet potatoes, flour and spice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Will make 2 to 3 loaves.

title: microwave dark cocoa brownies(double batch)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add oil and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or microwave 5:15 to 5:45 minutes.
Frost as desired.

title: raspberry earthquake bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

title: tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: divinity
directions: Leather furniture can be cleaned at home.
Use saddle soap or mild soap suds.
Rinse with a dairy cloth.
Follow with a leather conditioning dressing.
Never use furniture polish, oil, varnish, shellac, wax or even a treated duster on leather.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef; drain well.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles while the first mixture is simmering.

title: seasoned salad oil
directions: Shake ingredients in tightly covered jar.
Let stand at least 4 days.
Makes 1 cup dressing.

title: buttermilk donuts
directions: Mix sugar and eggs well; add cream.
Mix well, then add buttermilk and stir well.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill before rolling; cut and deep fry.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: world war ii pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add milk, butter and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan.
Mix syrup and boiling water.
Stir in cocoa and pour over batter.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Serve with cream.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter while preheating oven to 350°.
Mix graham cracker crumbs with butter and press on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with nuts, chocolate pieces and coconut.
Pour condensed milk over coconut.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: chicken and rice dish
directions: In 9 x 13-inch glass dish, lightly greased with oleo, layer 1/2 of yellow rice, white rice and the remaining yellow rice. Place chicken on rice.
Sprinkle with soup mix.
Place small pats of oleo over soup mix.
Slowly pour water over entire dish.
Cover dish with foil.
Cook in 300° oven for 45 minutes or until rice is done.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top just before taking out of oven.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Set aside.
Mix Crisco (do not melt), sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Add vanilla pudding mix (dry).
Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in chips. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: grandma's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: corn bread
directions: Heat oil in iron skillet or muffin tin.
Mix dry ingredients then add buttermilk.
Add small amount of hot oil into mixture, then pour back into hot skillet.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: seven can company casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except Chinese noodles.
Bake in large casserole 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.
Serve over Chinese noodles.
May be frozen.
Serves 12.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and dry tomatoes.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Add cheese, garlic and onion powder to flour.
Mix well.
Beat eggs.
Dip each tomato slice first in flour, then into the eggs and into the flour again.
Fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.
Remove to paper towel.
Sprinkle additional cheese on each slice.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate chips and coffee over low heat or in a microwave on low power.
After it's melted, add butter, cream and vanilla.
Good served over ice cream or pound cake.

title: uptown grits
directions: Cook grits in boiling salted water.
Melt butter and cheese together and add to grits.
Beat eggs.
Add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Add to other mixture and pour into greased casserole. Sprinkle crumbs over top and bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Serve with ham or pork chops.

title: upside-down rhubarb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put marshmallows in a 9-inch square pan. Mix together rhubarb and 3/4 cup sugar and put over the marshmallows. Cream together oleo, sugar and eggs.
Mix together flour and baking powder.
Mix milk and vanilla.
Add alternately the flour mixture and milk mixture to the creamed mixture.
Pour over rhubarb in pan. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool 5 minutes, then flip over onto serving plate.

title: sausage vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute sausage until done and drain.
Add all other ingredients except croutons.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with croutons and brown.
Easy and good! Serve with green vegetable and salad.

title: pork cake
directions: Mix raisins in boiling water.
Mix rest of dry ingredients. Add applesauce and sausage together with raisins and water, then add dry ingredients alternately after stirring well, until all ingredients are blended well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured tube pans and bake for 1 1/2 hours until straw comes out clean (about 375° preheated oven, then lowered to 350°).

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, onion and salt in 2 cups water, about 10 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Stir constantly until soup is hot and thickened.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Put in pan.
Pour ketchup on top. Bake in 350° oven 1 hour.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: Microwave Method:
Place melts and milk in a microwavable bowl and microwave for 1 minute.
Stir; if not melted, microwave 10 seconds at a time to dissolve.
When melted, stir until well blended.
Add marshmallow cream and pecans.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and allow to set.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook celery, onion and carrots until tender.
Add flour; cook one more minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in broth and milk; cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Add chicken and stuffing; toss to coat.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake five more minutes.

title: gail morgan's popcorn balls
directions: Microwave
butter, sugar and marshmallows for 2 1/2 minutes on High, then stir.
Microwave for 2 1/2 more minutes.
Pour over popcorn and shape into balls.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Put all ingredients into mixing bowl and beat well until well blended.
Pour into 3 prepared 9 inch pans and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats in separate bowl.
Let set 20 minutes. Cream brown sugar, white sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla together and add oats.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: zesty zucchini muffins
directions: Spray a muffin pan with vegetable spray.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix everything together.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ragsdale's barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll out walnut size.
Place one layer thick in pan and cover with sauce (recipe follows).
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: french mushroom soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, saute onions in butter about 5 minutes. Add mushrooms. Cook and stir 3 minutes. Remove and reserve a few mushroom slices for garnish. Add broth and vinegar.
Bring to a boil. Stir, cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Empty fruit and pie filling into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Melt butter and drizzle over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crystal bars
directions: Mix in order given (don't overbeat).
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 375° (don't overcook). Dough will be very stiff.
Spread in pan as best you can, but don't worry about full coverage.

title: six weeks bran muffins
directions: Bring water to a boil and add baking soda; let cool.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add water and soda mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk and flour.
In a large bowl, mix dates, nuts and cereal.
Add all ingredients together.
Makes 5 quarts.
Store in tight container in refrigerator.
Spoon into well-greased muffin tins without stirring.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
These will keep 6 weeks according to the recipe.
(Mine never did last that long.
We ate them first.)

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn into a brown paper grocery bag. Combine first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil in microwave.
Boil 2 minutes. Add soda and stir until foamy.
Pour over corn and shake.
Fold bag and put into microwave. Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove and shake. Return bag and microwave another 1 1/2 minutes more. Remove and shake.
Pour caramel corn on counter.
Let cool.

title: sugar cookie supreme
directions: Beat until fluffy:
the powdered sugar, margarine, cooking oil, granulated sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Blend well and chill until easy to handle. Roll in hand to size of walnuts.
Roll in sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Press out and sprinkle with sugar.
(Should be the size of a 50 cent piece.)
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: In skillet, melt margarine; add onion and saute until clear. Add uncooked broccoli; stir thoroughly.
Add soup; stir and simmer several minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz and let simmer.
Add cooked rice; stir and let simmer a few minutes.
Put in greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, uncovered.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In a small bowl, mix at medium speed, eggs and milk until frothy.
Beat in flour, sugar, baking powder and salt until smooth.

title: divinity rolls
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Heat.
Stir until dissolved. Boil over low heat until a little dropped in water almost forms a little ball, about 275°.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff.
Add hot syrup to beaten egg whites and beat until loses its gloss and is hard to mix.
Add vanilla; let stand until you can handle with hands.
Lightly grease hands with butter and form divinity logs. Chill until firm and dry on wax paper (2 hours).
Combine milk, 1/2 cup corn syrup and salt.
Cook these 3 ingredients over low heat, stirring constantly for 20 minutes until forms a soft ball and is caramel colored.
Have enough pecan halves ready to cover rolls after you spread on caramel mixture.
With knife spread length of roll with caramel, place on pecan halves, turning and doing same until all of roll is covered.
Place on wax paper.
A little work, but much better than those you purchase in stores.

title: lime punch
directions: Boil 3 cups water and 3 cups sugar until sugar dissolves. Dissolve Jell-O in 4 cups hot water.
Add lemon juice, extract and remaining water. Top with lime sherbet.

title: dried beef dip or spread
directions: Blend together and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: venison sausage and rice
directions: Brown venison.
Saute mushrooms and onion.
Combine all ingredients; season to taste with Tony's.

title: 9 layer salad
directions: Using a large bowl, place ingredients in layers as listed. Allow to set for 24 hours to blend flavors.
Can be served as a salad or fill half a pita pocket with salad mixture.

title: corned-beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni or spaghetti in boiling water until desired tenderness.
Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Put a layer of ingredients and top with bread crumbs; continue this alternating and finish with a topping of bread crumbs and dots of butter.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8. Season to taste.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix and vanilla pudding.
In another bowl, blend eggs with oil.
Add almond extract, hot water and poppy seed.
Blend liquids with dry ingredients about 4 minutes.
Pour in tube pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Make a glaze of powdered sugar and milk to drizzle over warm cake.

title: lynn's lima beans
directions: Soak beans for 8 hours. Wash and pick bad beans out. Fill the crock pot with water 3/4 full. Put beans and other ingredients in crock pot. Cook on 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Stir in sauce and water.
Mix well: the cheese, eggs and pepper.
Layer lasagna, cheese stuff and sauce alternately; begin and end with sauce.
Cover and bake 50 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.
Bake at 350°.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order given.
Chill.
Roll in balls and roll in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
These will fall and crack!

title: cheese cake
directions: With rolling pin, crush graham crackers until fine.
Pour crumbs into bowl.
Add confectioners sugar.
Add margarine.
Take hands and mix well and press into pan.

title: black bean soup
directions: In large pot, combine beans and broth.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer until beans are fork-tender (about 2 hours).
In large skillet, combine sherry or wine, onions and garlic.
Cook and stir until onions are tender.
Add to beans. Add carrots, celery, bay leaf, parsley, cumin, pepper and liquid smoke.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.

title: yummy slush punch
directions: Bring the water and sugar to a full boil. Stir in the Koolaid. In a blender, mix together the bananas and pineapple to a smooth consistency. Add to first mixture, then add in pineapple juice. Freeze. To serve mix with 7-Up or Sprite. Makes 6-7 quarts.

title: glug(hot drink)
directions: Bring to a boil.
Cut off and leave 1 hour before serving.

title: easy chocolate pudding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box and bake in a Bundt cake pan.
Allow to cool.
Slice the cake into 3 layers.
Prepare pudding mix as directed and allow to thicken, slightly.
Spread pudding between each layer of cake.
Ice the cake with Cool Whip.

title: raspberry mint crush
directions: Combine sugar, mint leaves and 1 cup boiling water. Let stand 5 minutes. Add 2 cups cold water and stir. Serve over ice. Makes 8 servings.

title: christmas fragrance punch
directions: Place cinnamon and cloves, along with pickling spice, in cheesecloth bag.
Put bag and all other ingredients in a large pan.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: one step cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9
x 13-inch pan; pour peaches in pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and milk.
Blend until smooth.
Pour over peaches.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: old-fashioned custard ice cream
directions: Put milk on medium heat in heavy pot.
Do not stir.
Let it heat until it makes a film.
Beat eggs, cornstarch and sugar until real frothy, then add to milk.
Stir constantly until the consistency of a cream sauce.
Remove from fire and add remaining ingredients.
Let cool, then put into ice cream freezer.

title: sausage cheddar quiche
directions: Line a 9-inch quiche dish with pastry or 1 unbaked pie crust. Place a piece of buttered tinfoil buttered side down over pie crust.
Press onto pastry shell (this keeps sides of shell from collapsing).
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Remove foil.
Prick shell and bake for 3 to 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mindy's manicotti
directions: Soak spinach until all sand is removed.
Set aside to dry. Brown beef and chopped onion.
Add sauces, both jars.
Tear spinach.
Add 2 handfuls to sauce.
Simmer while stuffing manicotti.
To stuff, mix 1 pint cottage cheese, 1 cup Parmesan cheese, egg and 1 handful finely torn spinach.
Stuff mixture into stuff-a-roni's and place in ungreased 13 x 5-inch or 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with sauce.
Use all sauce and bake, covered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add 1 egg at a time.
Beat well. Sift flour with spices and salt.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Fold in flour alternately with buttermilk mixture.
Add juice and mix in pecans and jam.
Pour into three well-greased and floured pans. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.

title: ruby red raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add raspberries and stir until berries are thawed and separated.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; chill until set.
Carefully spread with sour cream; chill.
Dissolve cherry jello in remaining boiling water; add pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Mix well.
Allow to thicken slightly.
Carefully spoon over sour cream mixture; chill.

title: colcannon soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onions and cabbage in enough water to cover. Next, add soup, milk and seasonings.
Heat.
Add crumbled bacon just before serving.
Makes approximately 8 servings.
The bacon makes it excellent!

title: cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Cook at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk for 15 minutes.
Stir in butter and seasonings.
Beat eggs and add, stirring in gently, but thoroughly.
Pour into buttered baking dish; bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: layered salad
directions: Shred
a
head	of
lettuce
in a large shallow bowl or glass baking
dish.
Layer
each	of
the following in order: onions, celery,
water chestnuts and peas.	Spread mayonnaise over all. Sprinkle with sugar, Parmesan cheese, seasoned salt and garlic powder.
Chill overnight (24 hours).

title: microwave italian chicken
directions: Place chicken in a covered dish. Sprinkle with Italian mix, along with garlic, salt and pepper.
Microwave on High for 45 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: salsa
directions: Mix liquids together.
Chop vegetables.
Add all other ingredients.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: tilsore tebondepiker (farm girl's dessert)
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and cinnamon with butter in warm frying pan. Brown very lightly.
Whip the cream.
Make alternate layers of crumbs, applesauce and whipped cream in a large, clear serving bowl.
Each layer should be about 1/4 inch high.
Top with whipped cream.

title: mom's veal cutlets
directions: Heat butter and oil in skillet. Add veal and brown. Stir in wine, salt, oregano, basil, parsley and pepper. Cook over low heat for 15 minutes. Baste frequently.
Place cutlets in shallow baking dish.
Pour sauce over cutlets and cover with cheese. Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 12 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: 5 cup frozen salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients well.
Put in 8-inch square dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with well drained maraschino cherries.
Serves 6 or 9.

title: green bean stroganoff
directions: Heat beans.
Combine other ingredients and pour over beans. Top with onion rings or crushed potato chips.

title: sausage ring
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Put in a greased (spray with Pam) 6 1/2-cup jello ring or Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Drain off excess fat before unmolding.

title: skier's chili(makes a lot and freezes well)
directions: In large pot, saute beef with green pepper, onion and garlic until beef is browned.
Add rest of ingredients, except kidney beans; simmer, covered, about 1 hour.
Stir in beans; simmer 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix liquid ingredients.
Combine all and cook over medium heat in saucepan stirring constantly.
Pour in 9 inch baked pie shell.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cornstarch to boil; stir until clear. Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Pour over sliced berries in crust.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: cranberry-raspberry punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice and ginger ale in a punch bowl.
Drop sherbet in scoops.
Serve immediately.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Cut in tiny pieces prior to cooking. Chop up onions in small pieces.
Add to bacon at last and cook onion until transparent.
Hold off heat.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck in skillet on stove.
Pour into crock-pot. Add all other ingredients.
Mix and cook on low for 6 to 12 hours. Pour over spaghetti, cooked according to directions on box.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: vanilla pie dessert
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle flour over butter evenly.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, confectioners sugar and water in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Spread over prepared pastry.
Combine pudding mix and milk in mixer bowl; beat until thickened.
Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Top with whipped topping.
Garnish with coconut and maraschino cherries.
Chill in refrigerator until serving time.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: mama sifford's divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo syrup until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then pour half of syrup mixture on egg whites, stirring constantly.
Put remaining syrup mixture back on stove; cook until it forms hard ball in cold water. Stir into first mixture, beat until it starts getting stiff; add flavoring and few pecans.
Pour into buttered square pan.
Must be very firm before you cut into squares.
Follow cooking time of syrup mixture according to recipe.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix beans, brown sugar, vinegar, catsup and mustard.
Fry onions with bacon.
Pour onion and bacon drippings in bean mixture. Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pepperoni pinwheels
directions: Open each package of crescent rolls.
Do not break apart at perforated lines.
Instead pinch together two crescent shapes to form a rectangle.
Each package produces two rectangular shapes.

title: donnas homemade v.8. juice
directions: Mix ingredients all together in a large kettle, simmer for 45 minutes.
Press threw a sieve, to remove seeds and skins, return to the pot and add 1/2 cup lemon juice and bring to a boil- Pour into jars.
Process in boiling water bath for 30 minutes.
Makes 7 quarts.
I usually double this recipe.

title: delicious swiss baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in a pan and add Swiss cheese to each piece of chicken.
Pour soup over top of cheese, then add stuffing on top. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate popcorn balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Remember that a little goes a long way, so use herbs sparingly.
You can always add more if you need later.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cut the cheese and melt in the oven.
Put other ingredients in bowl and add the melted cheese.
Mix well with hands.
Make small balls and put on ungreased cookie sheet and freeze.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion and egg; shape into 6 patties.
In skillet, brown patties (use shortening if necessary); pour off fat.
Blend in remaining soup and water.
Cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes or until done. Stir occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato turbate(a favorite served at children's schools)
directions: Prepare instant mashed potatoes according to directions on package.
Brown meat lightly.
Add onions and seasonings.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Add flour and mix well with meat mixture.
Stir and scrape bottom of pan.
Add bouillon stock to make proper consistency.
Drain off excess fat.
Layer meat and potatoes into a baking dish.
Brush top with melted butter and dust lightly with paprika.
Bake at 400° until brown on top, about 25 minutes.

title: sliced sweet potato pie
directions: Peel, slice and wash sweet potatoes.
Put in large stainless steel pot with 1/4 stick margarine to keep potatoes from turning dark; add sugar, salt and water.
Boil until tender on the edges. Add flour, stirring until dissolved.
Pour into the pie crust.

title: easy coconut cream pie(microwave)
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch in a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Mix well.
Microwave at High power for 10 to 12 minutes.
Stir after 5 minutes, then every 2 minutes until thickened.
Stir in oleo, extracts and coconut.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake at 350° for about 5 minutes or until brown.

title: white bread
directions: Mix potatoes, water and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add sugar to yeast and mix with mixture.
Add the milk and enough flour to make a smooth batter.
Let set until doubled and bubbly (about 1 hour).
Then add salt and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead well.
Place in a greased bowl; cover and let rise until doubled, then punch down and put in pans and let rise until double again.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 5 loaves.

title: caramel popcorn(microwave)
directions: Cook brown sugar, Karo, margarine and salt on High 3 minutes. Add soda; stir well until foamy.
Heat popped popcorn in grocery bag for 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour brown sugar mixture over popcorn in grocery bag.
Fold bag 2 times.
Microwave on High 1 minute. Shake bag.
Microwave 1 minute.
Shake again.
Microwave 1/2 minute.
Pour onto baking sheet.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Place in round baking pan and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool; crumble.
Combine tomatoes, pepper, onion, pickles and bacon bits; set aside.
Stir Miracle Whip and pickle juice together.
Layer in deep serving bowl, beginning with crumbled cornbread, Miracle Whip mixture and fresh vegetables.
Continue to layer topping with vegetable mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix 1 3/4 cup honey, eggs and vegetable oil; then add flour, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat well.
Add carrots, black walnuts and raisins (optional).
Bake in 3 (9-inch) cake pans or large, long pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken-fruit salad
directions: Gently toss together chicken, celery, grapes, pineapple, orange segments and 3 tablespoons of the pecans.
Mix salad dressing and salt with chicken mixture; chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves and garnish with remaining pecans.
Serves 6.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Makes 9-inch pie.

title: date bread
directions: Spoon soda over dates; add hot water, then let cool.
Mix shortening and sugar; add eggs, flour and nuts.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and margarine. Bake in 13 x 9 pan

at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Stir in strawberries. Chill slightly. Mix cream cheese and sugar. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread cream cheese mixture over pretzel mix. Add Jell-O layer. Chill. Best made night before.

title: sloppy joe bake
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, ketchup, brown sugar, mustard and heat to boiling.
Spoon into ungreased 9x13 baking dish.
Stir Bisquick, milk and eggs with a fork until blended.
Carefully pour mixture over beef.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on top of first mix.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Sprinkle extra sugar on top.
Cut into squares.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture boils. Add eggs, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook until thick.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Cool.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour in pie crust and chill.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: stuffed fillet of sole
directions: In skillet, saute onion in margarine.
Stir in the parsley, cucumber, hard-boiled eggs, cooked rice, salt and pepper.
Add milk to moisten.
Spoon this filling on fillets.
Roll to enclose filling and secure with toothpicks.
Place in baking dish. Drizzle butter over top.
Bake 45 minutes in 400° oven.

title: hash brown potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Beat together eggs and milk in a medium bowl; stir in hash browns, onion, salt and hot pepper sauce. Stir in 1 c. of the cheese and 1/2 of the bacon. Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake for 25-30 minutes or until center is set. Sprinkle remaining bacon and cheese
over top of pie and continue baking for 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese is melted. This dish can be refrigerated over night and baked the following morning.

title: grandmother hudson's chess pie
directions: Beat together as you add each ingredient on low speed.
Pour into a 9-inch standard unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Step 1:
Place frozen beef and tomato mixture in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover with casserole lid.

title: potato soup with lumps
directions: Add first four ingredients to soup pan.
Boil until potatoes are still slightly firm, then add milk and butter.
Simmer.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain grease.
Add chili beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Simmer until done.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in a 400° oven for 1 hour.
Cut in half and remove potato.
Add milk, butter, salt and pepper; beat until light and fluffy.
Pile lightly into shells.
Top with grated cheese.
Wrap for freezing if desired.
Just prior to serving, place under broiler until cheese melts and turns brown.

title: popover pizzas
directions: Cook meat, onion and butter until brown, then drain.
Stir sauce and seasonings into meat mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place Mozzarella on top; set aside.
Combine eggs, milk and oil; add flour and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Pour this batter over meat mixture in the pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt oleo and cocoa in saucepan. Add sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour and pecans. Mix well. Bake in a well-greased and floured 9 x 13 pan 30 minutes at 350°. As soon as you remove the cake from the oven, top
with marshmallow cream.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Layer cake, Dream Whip mixture, another layer of cake, strawberry glaze mixture and top with Cool Whip.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix together the sugar and flour.
Put on sliced peaches.
Put butter on, then dribble eggs over pie.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 375° and finish baking.

title: aunt bill's microwave candy
directions: Combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and butter.
Microwave for 2 1/2 minutes; stir and turn dish.
Return to oven for 2 minutes, or until soft ball forms in cold water or it tests 236° on candy thermometer (do not put thermometer in microwave).
Add vanilla; beat with electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Watch closely. Stir in pecans.
Spread in buttered 12 x 7-inch dish.
Cool; cut into pieces.

title: raisin-spice muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, allspice and raisins; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients until well blended. Stir flour mixture into milk mixture just until flour is moistened (batter may be lumpy).
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 24 minutes or until muffins are golden brown at 400°.

title: hot chip beef dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and next 6 ingredients.
Spoon into oven dish.
Mix butter and pecans and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rick's breakfast
directions: The night before, grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer bread, cheese and meat.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the layered mixture.
Cover with foil and place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: lemon angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating until very stiff and glossy.
Bake in glass pie dish.
Build up sides to form a hollow space for filling.
Bake in preheated oven at 275° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven; leave in oven for 1 hour.
Remove and cool.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef until done.
Drain.
Blend all ingredients in large pot on stove.
Cook on low-medium heat until desired consistency is attained, usually 1 hour.

title: grandma o'brien's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and flavoring.
Add chocolate chips, nuts, oatmeal and sifted flour mixture.
Bake at 350° to 375° until brown.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion in olive oil until onion is clear. Combine with browned and drained meat. Add rest of ingredients.
Stir.
Simmer 2-3 hours.

title: sweet potato dixie bake
directions: Combine sweet potatoes and eggs; mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour in 8-inch round baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Grate carrots, cover and set aside.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl mix together vegetable oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add carrots, pineapple and nuts; fold in well (do not beat).
Divide in 3 (9-inch) cake pans that have been oiled and floured.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Use our favorite icing (cream cheese, etc.).

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, until golden brown.

title: caramel bars
directions: Mix the cake mix, butter and 1/3 c. evaporated milk together. Press 1/2 of of the mixture in a 9x13 pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes and cool. Melt the caramels and evaporated milk in the microwave until smooth. Pour over crust. Sprinkle 1 cup of chocolate chips and 1 cup pecans over the caramel. Dot remaining cake mix batter over the top. Bake 350 degrees for 17 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix all cake ingredients well. Bake for 35 minutes at 350° in square pan.

title: how to make kraut
directions: Shred cabbage.
Pack in quart jars.
Add 1 teaspoon salt per quart.
Fill your jar with cold water and seal jar tight.
Store in cool place.
Kraut will be ready in 2 weeks to eat.

title: mac bean and bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray an 8-inch square baking dish with cooking spray.
Mix noodles, beans and tomatoes together.
Add 1 cup of Cheddar cheese and put in dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Stir water and yeast until yeast dissolves.
Set aside.
In large bowl, stir flour, sugar, margarine and salt until mixed. Add to flour mixture, one egg and yeast mixture.
Mix on well floured board and put in large bowl in refrigerator.
Can be kept in refrigerator 2 or 3 days.
Take what you need and make into rolls.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain fruit; heat juice from fruit and add boiling water to make 2 cups.
Pour over Jell-O and let cool.
Add Coca-Cola. Chill until partially set.
Fold in fruits, nuts and celery.
Pour in mold and chill in refrigerator until firm.

title: grandma's apple pie
directions: Cook, covered, stirring frequently, until rice is tender and milk is almost absorbed.

title: nancy saunders' cheese cake
directions: Mix cake according to box directions.
Spread in greased 11 x 16-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; spread on top of batter. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
During the last 15 minutes, sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, pepper and mushrooms over medium-high heat.
Layer ground beef mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Top with layer of sliced potatoes.
Heat soups together to boiling point and pour over potatoes.
Continue layering ground beef and potatoes, topping with soup mixture. Bake at 375° until potatoes are done.

title: cannellini bean soup(fast, easy and good)
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add onion and garlic; saute until golden.
Add beans, water and seasonings.
Cook, uncovered, until boiling, stirring often.
Simmer over low heat, uncovered, until thick, about 1/2 hour.
Stir in butter.
Makes about 6 servings. Add cooked pasta, if desired.
If serving hot with pasta, pass with grated cheese and good, crunchy bread.
Also delicious cold without the pasta.
Top with additional chopped raw onions (white or green) and hot garlic bread.
Delicious!

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Add flour and mix well.
Add baking powder.
Stir in milk.
Add the melted margarine.
Add vanilla and coconut, then add nuts.
Mix well all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheesy shrimp spread
directions: Using a fork, blend softened cream cheese with drained and rinsed shrimp.
Tur into a serving bowl.
Before serving, top with shrimp cocktail sauce.
Serve on crackers.

title: slush
directions: Bring to a boil the first 2 ingredients.
Cool 15 minutes. Pour into freezer container.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Freeze 24 hours.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Spray crock-pot with nonstick oil. Place chicken in bottom of crock-pot. In a separate bowl, mix soup, sour cream and onion soup mix and pour over chicken.	Cook on low for 7 hours. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Put into crock-pot and stir.
Heat and serve with your favorite chips.

title: lythonia's soup
directions: Cook until wilted.
Put in jars and process 25 minutes on 10 pounds pressure.

title: cleaning wipes
directions: Mix the solution per ingredients; pour over paper towels in your container.
Seal container.
In about 1 hour, it is ready to use.
Pull wipes from the center.
Not only do these save money, but they are great to use, too.

title: pasta noodle salad
directions: Mix noodles and meats in a bowl.
Add olives, tomatoes, onions and shredded cheese to taste.
Pour on creamy Italian dressing and mix.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts. After mixing well, add nuts. Stir well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: In large bowl, combine sour cream, minced onion, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Peel and thinly slice cucumbers; add and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Best if stands overnight.
Then drain off most of the liquid.

title: sweet-sour green beans
directions: Brown bacon strips until crisp.
Cook chopped onion in bacon fat until yellow.
Stir in flour.
Add and bring to a boil the vegetable liquid, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir in cooked green beans.
Stir gently until heated through. Serve with crisp bacon sprinkled over top.

title: cherry topped cheesecake pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter; mix well.
Press into bottom and sides of 8-inch pie pan.
Chill 1 hour.

title: texas millionaire candy
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and bring to a boil. Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from fire and add remaining ingredients. Fold together for 1 minute or until thoroughly mixed.
Drop from teaspoon on wax paper.
Work fast before it becomes too hard.
Be sure to place wax paper on table before mixing.
Be ready to drop fast.
Makes 6 pounds.

title: pork chops and lima beans
directions: Salt and pepper chops and brown.
Set aside.
Stir over medium heat the remaining ingredients, until sauce thickens and lima beans thaw.
Arrange chops in sauce.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 to 45 minutes, until chops and beans are tender.
Do not boil.
Serve over 3 cups cooked rice.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix together; pour into large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mom's broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Also can add chunks of ham or chicken.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients with a little milk, then mix this with the remaining milk and boil and stir until thick.
Mix small amount of thickened mixture with egg yolks and put this back in the thickened mixture.
Add butter and vanilla and cook a little longer.
Add 1/2 cup shredded coconut.
Put in baked pie shell or graham cracker crust.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix together and top with Cheddar and Jack cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: healthy crunch
directions: Spread crackers in a large jelly roll pan. Chop pecans and sprinkle over crackers.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add sugar and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan before they cool completely. Break into sections.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and cool.
Mix lightly with remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: super burgers
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, mix well and shape into 4 patties.
Grill over medium heat to desired doneness, turning once.
Serve on buns.

title: icebox cake
directions: Cake is easier to work with if it's a day old.
Slice cake crosswise into about 4 layers.
Spread pudding mix (made up) between each layer.
Whip the whipping cream to a peak; add 1 teaspoon vanilla and sugar to taste.
Spread over top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle nuts on top and sides of cake.
Refrigerate (keeps several days).
I usually keep mine in a Tupperware container while in refrigerator.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except flour, then add flour.
Shape cookies onto a nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on a paper towel.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water and cook until clear.
Add peach jello and cook until thick.
Cool; pour over sliced fresh peaches in a cooked and cooled pie shell.
Chill until set.
Cool, delicious and refreshing.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: almondine peas and carrots
directions: Cook celery in boiling salted water until tender but crisp; drain.
Lightly brown almonds in butter.
Add onions, peas and celery.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Let set 1/2 hour, then refrigerate.

title: crispy onion baked chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
Combine bread crumbs and soup mix in a large zip top plastic bag.
Seal and shake well.
Brush chicken breasts and salad dressing.
Place chicken breasts, 1 at a time, in bag.
Seal and shake to coat.
Arrange chicken on an ungreased rack in a broiler pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done. Makes 4 servings.

title: catalina chicken
directions: Put chicken in a microwaveable casserole dish.
Pour Catalina salad dressing over chicken.
Slice onion and bell pepper in rings, then layer on top of chicken.
Cover and cook in microwave for 15 minutes, then rotate 1/2 turn, then cook 15 more minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Use a food processor for chopping.
Mix with hands, form into ball and chill.
Serve with variety of crackers.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Drain berries.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Combine egg, milk and melted butter in a small bowl.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir lightly just until liquid is absorbed.
Batter will be lumpy.
Gently fold in berries.
Spoon in 12 medium muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: easter tea cakes topped with honey
directions: Combine butter, sugar, cream and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer just until blended.
Increase speed to medium and beat until very well blended.
Combine flour, cinnamon and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture on low speed; beat just until blended.
Add nuts.

title: sliced sweet potato pie
directions: Roll out 2/3 of pastry and place in bottom of 10-inch square baking dish.
Combine sweet potatoes and sugar.
Place in crust. Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour milk over this and dot with
butter.
Roll out remaining pastry and cut into strips. Layer strips across dish in lattice pattern.
Sprinkle small amount of sugar and nutmeg on top of crust and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown.

title: lazy eclairs
directions: Boil the water and butter.
Add flour; mix until it forms a ball.
Add the eggs, mixing one at a time with wooden spoon.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry or cherry jello in 2 cups boiling water. Put nuts in bottom of Bundt pan.
Add a bit of jello and pie filling mixture; chill to set nuts.
Add remaining jello mixture. Top with small marshmallows; chill until firm.
Dissolve lemon jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add a small amount of lemon jello to the cream cheese and Miracle Whip in a separate bowl.
Mix with electric beater until smooth.
Add remaining lemon jello and can of crushed pineapple with juice to the chilled cherry mixture.
Chill several hours.

title: granny's banana croquet
directions: Peel and cut in half each banana.
Coat each banana with mayonnaise.
Roll each banana in nuts, evenly coating. Refrigerate.

title: friendship pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand and cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Set aside.
Mix coconut, pecans and margarine (melted) and toast at 350°, stirring every 5 minutes, until brown (about 12 to 13 minutes) and then cool.

title: honey glaze for chicken or chops
directions: Pierce meat with a fork.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over meat and marinate for at least 30 minutes (or overnight).
Grill or broil meat, using the marinade to baste or bake meat in sauce.

title: basic ravioli dough
directions: Combine all ingredients and knead dough on a lightly floured board until smooth and elastic.
Cover and let rest for 30 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out very thin into the shape of a rectangle.
Trim to shape by cutting with a knife, if necessary.
Lightly mark out 2-inch squares on the dough.
Place 1 teaspoon of filling in center of each square.
Roll out second piece of dough and carefully place over the top of the first. Lightly press down around mounds of filling and cut into 2-inch squares with pastry cutter.
It may help to seal the dough by sprinkling lightly with water before placing top over the filling. Cook in boiling, salted water until they rise to the top.
Remove with slotted spoon and serve as any pasta.

title: hamburger ring
directions: Mix ingredients in order given and pack into buttered 8-inch ring mold.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn onto platter.
Fill center with fluffy rice, peas or sauteed mushrooms.
Yields 6 servings.
Using recipe, pile meat mixture into greased muffin pans, rounding tops.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.
When serving these individual meat loaves, use A.1. sauce to make the meat more tasty or any other sauce you wish.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Blend together softened cream cheese and yogurt until smooth. Chill. Serve as a dip with fresh fruit (strawberries, fresh pineapple and melon).

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice as thin as possible.
Chop onions and peppers.
Combine with cucumbers and salt.
Let stand 3 hours. Drain. Combine vinegar, sugar and spices. Bring to boil.
Add drained cucumbers.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Pack while hot into sterilized jars and seal.

title: aunt daudies' fruit cake
directions: Soften margarine.
In very large bowl, mix by hand the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and orange juice. Add candied fruit, nuts, dates and coconut.
Mixture will be stiff.
Place in greased pans.
Will make several small cakes. Fill pans to about 2/3 full.
Bake in 225° oven (no higher) 3 hours or until light brown.
Will store well for 2 to 3 months. Store, tightly covered.

title: cherry almond crunchers
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix cereal, condensed milk and almond extract in a large bowl until well blended. Line 13 x 9 baking pan with foil, extending over edges to form handles.

title: knepfla soup
directions: In 6-quart Dutch oven, bring water, 3 rounded tablespoonfuls chicken soup base, onion and bay leaf to a boil.
Mix remaining ingredients and cut small pieces into boiling mixture.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Add 1 cup cream, 2 cups milk and 1/2 to 3/4 cup instant potatoes.
Simmer until done.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt, oil and Kool-Aid in a bowl.
Stir in boiling water until smooth.
Put on counter and knead several minutes. Store in Ziploc bag.
Smells good.

title: green bean & shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Combine green beans, corn, soup, cheese, sour cream and salt and pepper. Place in a greased shallow 2 qt casserole dish. Combine crushed crackers, margarine and
almonds. Sprinkle over top. Bake at 400° uncovered for 25 minutes.

title: baked brisket
directions: Slice the onions and put in the bottom of a roaster.
Sprinkle with paprika and Lawry's salt.
Trim the brisket some and place, fat side up, on top of the onions and sprinkle more paprika and Lawry's salt on top.
Place in a 450° to 500° oven, uncovered, for 1/2 hour.
Pour a bottle of Pepsi-Cola over the roast and reduce the oven heat to 325°.
Cover with foil and bake until fork-tender, 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours, depending on size of brisket.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Combine flour and milk; cook until thick.
Let cool.
Add sugar, Crisco, butter, salt and vanilla.
Beat together until fluffy, like whip cream.
Plenty of frosting for large layer cake or large loaf cake.

title: mrs. mosser's breakfast cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add shortening, milk, unbeaten egg and vanilla, one at a time.
Beat all ingredients well for 2 minutes.
Use greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hot artichoke and crabmeat dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix cream cheese and

mayo until smooth, add garlic. Chop artichokes, crabmeat, green onions, and parmesan cheese, add to cream cheese, mayo mixture. Add 1 teaspoon lemon zest and black pepper. Bake 25-30 minutes. Sprinkle with red peppers and additional green onions.

title: tuna delight
directions: Broil.
Can serve as many as you want.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish; top with 8 to 12 ounces Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for approximately 1/2 hour or until Mozzarella cheese is melted.

title: anise cookies
directions: Mix well in order given.
Use a cookie press. Decorate with colored sugar, if desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil diced potatoes.
Let cool.
Dice cucumbers, onion and eggs.
Add more mayonnaise than mustard (only a little).
Do this to your own taste.
Combine with boiled, drained potatoes.
Stir well.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Use as a dip for fresh fruit, such as apples, pineapple, grapes, etc.
Makes 2 cups.

title: green gumbo(for cajuns only)
directions: Make a roux in a large pot (add water to make thin or thick gumbo as desired).
Add next 3 ingredients.

title: walnut butter balls
directions: Mix with fingers until it works into a mass.
Pinch off bits and roll in palm of hand into tiny balls.
Bake in fairly hot 350° oven for about 10 to 15 minutes.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: pea picking cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together until well blended.
Divide batter in 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch squares.
Mix soups, onions, milk and chilies together.

Butter casserole dish and put 2 tablespoons juice from chicken in bottom. Place layers of tortillas, chicken and soup mixture, ending with grated cheese and let set overnight in refrigerator to blend flavors.
Bake, covered with foil, at 300° for about 90 minutes. Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 12 people.

title: cornflake no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Add peanut butter and butter.
Remove from heat, pour over 6 cups cornflakes.
Stir until covered.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper or a greased cookie sheet.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Mix it with all other ingredients in order: fryer, onion, green beans, mushroom soup, pimento, water chestnuts and mayonnaise.
Put in dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: May also use blueberry filling.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Put rhubarb in casserole dish.
Cover with sugar, dry jello and cake mix.
Cover with water.
Bake at 350° approximately 3/4 hour.

title: chocolate candy roll
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly.
Stir in powdered sugar and beaten egg.
Cool.
Fold in nuts and marshmallows.
Stir until well coated.
Shape soft candy into 2 rolls.
Coat rolls with coconut. Wrap in waxed paper.
Store in freezer until needed.
Cut into slices to serve.

title: classic macaroni salad
directions: In a small bowl, mix together mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, place cooked and drained macaroni, celery, green pepper, onion and flaked tuna fish.

Add mayonnaise mixture and mix thoroughly. Chill for at least 2 hours before serving (or mix together macaroni and chopped vegetables and refrigerate overnight and just before serving, add mayonnaise mixture and mix well).

title: chocolate devil's food cake(yields 12 servings)
directions: In saucepan mix cocoa, egg yolk and 1 cup milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Or put cocoa, egg yolk and 1 cup of milk in microwave bowl and whisk.
Cook in microwave 1 minute.
Stop and whisk.
Cook 1 more minute, stop and whisk.
Cook 1 more minute and stop and whisk.
May need 30 more seconds to 1 more minute to make thick.
If so, do 30 seconds at a time.
Set aside until cool.

title: apricot cheesecake
directions: Combine butter and sugar in a medium saucepan over medium high heat.
Stir constantly and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla wafer crumbs.
Press crumb mixture into bottom of an ungreased 9 inch spring form pan and chill.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except blueberries.
Blend until smooth.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in buttered pie dish on 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients
except crackers.
Pour over crackers. Mix well and let set for at least 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Shape into a ball.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and run on slowest speed until smooth.
This is good on small crackers and on rye bread for appetizers.

title: delicious dessert
directions: Mix together cream cheese and Cool Whip thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all fruits.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk and mix well.
Spray pan (loaf pan) with Pam and bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: granny stelter's banana pudding
directions: Separate egg whites; beat 3 egg yolks then mix 1/4 c. milk with yolks. Combine sugar, flour, salt. Add to eggs and milk; then add 1 c. milk cook in double boiler till thick.
Add 1 tsp vanilla. Cool slightly, beat the egg whites and fold into mixture. Add bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches in a bowl and add about 1/4 cup water.
Add sugar to taste.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together; pour over melted margarine.
Spoon peaches evenly over batter; pour juice over this.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Put all these vegetables through food grinder, using coarse blade.
Put in colander or cloth bag and drain overnight.

title: greek salad
directions: Wash and chop vegetables. Put all vegetables in a bowl. Crumble Feta cheese over top.
Add olives. Sprinkle oregano over top. Pour liquids over all ingredients. Mix, cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Pour milk over grated potatoes as soon as grated.
Mix sugar, oleo, eggs, juice and spices.
Add milk and potatoes; cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ginger tea
directions: Peel ginger root slices into tissue-thin slice.
Crush.
Add to water. Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 18 to 20 minutes.
Mix cinnamon and sugar, stir into ginger root mixture until dissolved. Remove ginger root, discard.
Cut walnuts into fine pieces.
Cut pine nuts into small pieces.
Pour ginger tea into cup.
Add small amount of nuts and dates to each cup.

title: creamettes cheese bake
directions: Melt butter over low heat and add flour, milk, salt and pepper.
Combine white sauce with cooked Creamettes.
Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: shrimp dip pate
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into a ball.
Place on serving platter surrounded by crackers.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Soften cream cheese with milk.
Combine all ingredients in small baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot on crackers.
Serves 10 to 12 persons.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate in double butter.
Separate eggs.
Beat whites until stiff.
Add superfine sugar and beat again.
Beat egg yolks very slightly.
Add to chocolate and mix well.
Fold in egg whites.
Spoon into glasses.

title: ultimate chocolate cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first seven ingredients; mix well. Stir in chocolate chips. Coat a 10-in. fluted tube pan with nonstick cooking spray and dust with flour; add batter.

title: creole corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Saute onion & bell pepper. Add corn, sugar, salt, pepper & pimentos. Cool & add cheese & well beaten eggs. Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole & set in pan of hot water.Bake 35 minutes at 350 degrees. Serve at once.

title: dirt cake
directions: Items needed:
Clean 8-inch clay or plastic flower pot, small dirt scoop for decoration and serving, and something to cover hole in bottom of flower pot (plastic lid from Cool Whip).

title: wild rice venison casserole
directions: Dredge venison cubes in flour.
Brown in butter over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; continue cooking 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add remaining ingredients except rice. Bring to a boil. Add raw rice.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour or longer, if needed, stirring occasionally.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Prepare soft dough.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Blend in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal. Stir in milk to make a soft dough.
Drop spoonfuls of dough over hot fruit filling.

title: larapin cake
directions: Prepare cake by combining first four ingredients.
Bake in two nine-inch round pans at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Split layers when cool.
Prepare the icing by combining the last three ingredients.
Spread on all layers.

title: any time broccoli cheese sauce
directions: Combine soup and milk.	Heat over medium heat until hot and bubbling, stirring often.
Serve over vegetables, such as broccoli,
cauliflower and carrots.
Makes 1 1/2 cups. Preparation time:
3 minutes.

title: hot chicken
directions: Put chicken into a casserole dish large enough to hold it. Mix all other ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in microwave oven, about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir chicken from bottom to top frequently.
This recipe can be baked in a regular oven for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter in a large skillet.
Cover until onions are tender.
Uncover; cook until brown.
Stir in broth and water. Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Put soup in ovenproof dishes.
Place croutons in each; sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour, 375° for 15 minutes.
Use loaf pan.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour. Add beaten eggs. Mix melted oleo and cocoa. Add melted mixture to sugar, flour and eggs. Add vanilla. Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Saute onion and pepper in 1 tablespoon of the margarine.
Mix other ingredients together with the onion and pepper; gently fold in the squash.
Top with another 3/4 cup of grated Cheddar cheese (in addition to the 3/4 of cheese already in the mixture) and cracker crumbs which have been buttered with margarine or cooking oil.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream sandwich
directions: Put the Cool Whip between two of the chocolate graham crackers. Then freeze overnight.
Wrap each one in foil paper so that they are easy to get apart.

title: bacon wraps
directions: Wrap 1/2 slice raw bacon around a single cracker.
Continue until a cookie sheet is filled.
Sprinkle a heavy amount of Parmesan cheese over crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar, flour (Gold Medal), eggs and flavors (alternate 1/2 cup flour and 1 egg).
Beat well.
Put in cold oven.
Turn to 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice crispy and marshmallow bars(microwave)
directions: Heat marshmallows and butter in microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Pour in half of the cereal and stir until coated; add the other half and stir until coated.
Pour the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and press the mixture down evenly. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: grasshopper dessert squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place ice cream in refrigerator for 20 minutes to soften.
In small bowl, mix crushed cookies and melted butter; stir to completely coat cookies.
Press cookies into bottom of 8 x 8 glass dish.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes; cool completely and place in freezer.

title: graham cracker fudge
directions: Mix fine graham cracker crumbs (about 16) and flour together; set aside.
In saucepan, over low heat, melt oleo, milk and sugar; bring to rolling boil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add crumb-flour mixture, nuts, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool; cut in squares.

title: date and nut bread
directions: With fork, mix walnuts, dates, soda and salt.
Add shortening and water; let stand 20 minutes.
Start heating oven to 350°. Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
With fork, beat eggs; beat in vanilla, sugar and flour.
Mix in date mixture until just blended. Turn into pan.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cook in pan 10 minutes. Remove to wire rack to finish cooling.
Wrap in foil and store overnight before slicing.

title: fork and spoon soup
directions: Melt butter in 5-quart pot.
Add onions and garlic.
Cover, wilt slowly, about 7 minutes.
Add stock; bring to boil.
Stir in elbow macaroni; bring to boil again.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Add tomatoes, seasonings, lobster tails and escarole.
Simmer, covered, 8 minutes.
Stir in grated cheese.
Serves 8.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, dates, nuts, milk and baking powder; mix well.
Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: oriental vegetable salad
