directions: Crush noodles; mix with slaw, onions, almonds and sunflower seeds.
Put dressing on just before serving.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks with a hand beater.
Add remaining ingredients except egg whites; beat until smooth.
(For thinner pancakes, stir in 2 to 4 tablespoons additional buttermilk.)
Fold in egg whites gently.
Grease a heated griddle, if necessary.
(To test griddle, sprinkle with a few drops of water.
If bubbles skitter around, heat is just right.)
Pour batter onto hot griddle for each pancake.
Cook until puffed and dry around edges.
Turn and cook other sides until golden brown.
Makes about sixteen 4-inch pancakes.

title: lemon pineapple pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and margarine; press onto the bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until set and lightly browned;
cool on a wire rack.
tags: sugar-free cook and serve vanilla pudding mix

title: red raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in
boiling water.
Add 7-Up and rest of ingredients.
Pour in mold and chill.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cut in shortening with 2 knives or pastry blender.
Add milk all at once to make a soft dough.
Place on floured board; knead lightly. Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with floured biscuit cutter. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° until done, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 14 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: easy popcorn balls
directions: Melt butter, then pour in marshmallows.
Stir continually until marshmallows are melted.
Pour over popcorn. Stir well. Put small amount of grease or butter on cleaned hands and shape into balls.

title: penuche
directions: Blend sugars, cream of tartar and salt in large saucepan.
Add milk and cream and stir until sugar is almost dissolved.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar is completely dissolved before boiling point is reached.
Boil, stirring occasionally until soft ball forms in cold water or 234° to 235°. Remove from heat; cool without stirring to 149° or until bottom of pan is just warm.
Beat until candy loses its gloss and becomes creamy.
Add nuts.
At first sign of stiffening pour into buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 1 3/4 pounds.

title: sorghum suckers
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water together.
Bring to boil and cook over low to medium heat to 310°.
Remove from heat.
Add sorghum and stir to mix thoroughly.
Pour into lightly oiled metal molds. Insert sucker sticks and cool.
Remove from old, wrap in waxed paper and store in airtight containers.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Fry bacon in large frying pan.
Remove bacon from pan and add vinegar and sugar to the grease.
Cook until well blended.
Add onion and as much lettuce as the pan will hold.
(May be head of lettuce cut up or leaf lettuce.) Cook in liquid, tossing frequently, until lettuce begins to wilt.
Take off heat and add the bacon, cut up.
Serve immediately.

title: carolyn's zucchini muffins
directions: Beat oil and sugar; add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add zucchini and pineapple.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well. Fill slightly greased muffin tins about 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: sunshine shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Measure all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl; mix with hand well.
By mixing and stirring with hand, apples won't sink to bottom of pan.
Line inside of tube pan with wax paper before pouring batter into pan; bake for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: rolled steak
directions: Mix all ingredients except olive oil (put as much as needed). Brown steak in olive oil, stuff with dressing, tie with string. Simmer in sauce for 2 1/2 hours.
Serve with spaghetti.
(See sauce recipe for steak!)

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat the strawberries and Jell-O over low heat until Jell-O is dissolved, stirring several times.
Mix pudding mix and 2 cups milk together.
Stir in the sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer the vanilla wafers, pudding and strawberry mixture.
Chill.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in small casserole. Sprinkle 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with any corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: stuffed mushrooms parmigiana
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Remove stems.
Finely chop.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion, pepperoni, green pepper, garlic and chopped stems.
Cook until vegetables are tender, but not brown.
Add cracker crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt, oregano and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in chicken broth.
Spoon into caps.
Place caps on baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Can also add crab meat or shrimp.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: With a vegetable peeler, remove the orange portion of the peel of 1 orange; set aside.
Completely peel and section both oranges. Using a food grinder with a coarse blade (or a food processor), grind reserved orange peel, orange sections and cranberries.
Stir in sugar and nuts.
Chill for several hours.
Makes approximately 3 1/2 cups.

title: tomato-corn scallop
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Drain whole kernel corn, reserving 2 tablespoons liquid.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix good.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes or longer at 325°.
Top with whip cream.

title: low-fat pumpkin bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine 1 cup of the flour, brown sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, salt, soda, nutmeg and cloves or ginger.
Add pumpkin, milk, eggs or egg substitute and applesauce. Beat on low speed until blended, then on high for 2 minutes. Add remaining 1 cup flour and beat well.
Stir in raisins. Spray loaf pan with nonstick spray.
Pour batter in pan and bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Boil chicken for 30 minutes or until done.
Bone and skin chicken and cut into pieces.
In a large bowl mix enchilada sauce, chilies, olives, soup and chicken.
In a casserole dish, put down a layer of tortillas.
Pour on a layer of sauce and cover with both kinds of cheese.
Bake covered for 30 minutes at 350°. Turkey or ground beef can be substituted.

title: 3 in one dinner
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Put in bottom of casserole dish. Place sliced potatoes over hamburger, then pour in soup and water. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham salad filling
directions: Tip:
Ground canned luncheon meat may be substituted for ham.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add sugar.
Let stand while mixing jello. Let jello cool.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in refrigerator.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain. In large skillet, brown hamburger and cook onions and peppers until tender.
Drain.
Add mushroom and tomato soups.
Stir until blended.
Add macaroni; mix well.
Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese melts and begins to brown.

title: cranberry cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cream butter and sugars, stir in milk and orange juice.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons about 2 inches apart onto a greased baking sheet. Makes 11 dozen cookies.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Boil wine vinegar, water, lemon, peppercorns and bay leaves together for 5 minutes.
Rub beef with salt and pepper.
Cut garlic into slivers and insert into meat.
Place meat in nonmetallic container and cover with hot marinade and sliced onion. Refrigerate.
Turn meat daily, 4 to 5 days.

title: zucchini cheese muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Blend well. Add onion, bacon, cheese and zucchini.
Mix egg, milk and oil. Blend well.
Add wet mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir until just moistened.
Fill greased or paper lined muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yield: 12 muffins.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: pineapple paradise pie
directions: Soften butter in mixing bowl. Add sugar, flour and coconut. mix well; press into bottom of 13 x 9 inch pan. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes until brown. Crumble. Press 2 c. into 9 inch pie pan. Reserve remaining mixture.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix Jiffy cake mix as box directs.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together and spread over cooled cake the pineapple.
Spread over pudding mixture.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: apple pie with cream cheese
directions: For Crust:
Mix first 4 ingredients together well.
Press into an 8 or 9-inch pie pan.

title: klondike candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and cream together to soft ball stage.
Pour over the mixture of corn flakes, coconut, peanuts and Rice Krispies.
Spread mixture on a greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Add flour to hot oil in Dutch oven, stirring constantly until roux is dark golden brown.
Stir in celery, peppers, onions and garlic.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes and water, simmering 15 minutes.
Add shrimp, crab meat, sausage, okra and seasonings.
Simmer 20 more minutes.
Serve over cooked rice. A pint of oysters may be added with shrimp, if you like.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; debone it. Combine all soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cut cooked chicken, then put into sauce. Stir over medium heat until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with crunched Doritos.
Pour mixture over Doritos.
Sprinkle with Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses.
Bake in 350° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Then enjoy.

title: icebox pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix next three ingredients and spread on first layer.
Mix the rest of the ingredients well and add to second layer.
Top with the rest of the Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.
Serve.

title: meat balls
directions: Foil line pans; mix and shape.
Put in flat one layer.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook 1 hour. Stir to keep from sticking. fill sterilized jars with mixture and seal.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake according to directions.
Cool and cut in half. Make pudding according to directions.
Break up half of cake into bottom of punch bowl.
Put half vanilla pudding over cake.
Put 1 can crushed pineapple over pudding.
Put 1 can cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Put 1 Cool Whip over cherry pie filling.
Put 1 package nuts over Cool Whip.
Repeat, starting with other half cake.

title: joanne's peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, raw peanuts, Karo, water and salt and cook without stirring until peanuts start popping, then stir until they stop popping or until the peanuts look done.
Remove from stove and add 1 teaspoon soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix together well and pour into pan.
Makes a large amount of candy.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt into a large bowl.
Combine egg, buttermilk and oil in medium bowl.
Stir liquid ingredients into dry ingredients until moistened.

title: sweet potato-apple casserole
directions: Simmer the apples in a small amount of water for 10 minutes. Place sweet potatoes (cut in half lengthwise) in a greased casserole.
Place sliced apples on top.
Sprinkle cinnamon and brown sugar on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes in covered casserole.

title: herbed biscuits
directions: Mix butter and herbs.
Cut each biscuit in half.
Form into balls.
Roll in butter mixture.
Place in baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican dip with chips
directions: Layer in order in casserole dish and serve with taco chips.

title: my mom's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco until dissolved.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to first mixture.
Add extracts.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Set temperature to 325° and bake for 90 minutes.
Yields
15 to 18 servings.

title: broccoli-onion deluxe
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Cook onion (or cauliflower) until tender and drain.
Melt half of the butter in a saucepan. Blend in the flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly. Reduce heat and blend in cream cheese.
Pour in cooked vegetables and toss lightly.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with shredded cheese.
Melt remaining butter. Add bread crumbs and toss.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Cream together shortening and butter.
Add vanilla.
Add sugar, 1 cup at a time, beating well on low or medium speed. Scrape sides and bottom of bowl often.
Add milk or water.
Mix 5 minutes until light and fluffy on medium speed.
Makes approximately 3 cups.
Double recipe if you wish to make rose or icing characters.
Leftovers can be put in an airtight container and refrigerate up to 2 weeks.

title: oatmeal crispies cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown. Makes approximately 6 dozen cookies.

title: swiss steak
directions: Season both sides
of steaks with garlic powder, pepper and salt.
Heat 1
teaspoon
butter
in
a
10-inch
nonstick skillet over medium-high
heat;
heat
until
butter is foamy. Add 4 steaks and cook about 2 minutes per side, until browned. Remove to plate.
Repeat with remaining butter and steaks.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken; drain and debone.
Put chicken in bottom of dish.
Pour mixture of soup and sour cream over chicken.
Pour crushed crackers on top, then pour melted margarine on top. Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil fryer in enough water to make 2 quarts of stock.
Saute onions, pepper, celery and garlic in margarine.
Add 1 quart stock and tomatoes.
Simmer together 5 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat strawberries, sugar and strawberry jello.
Mix together vanilla pudding, milk, sour cream and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, strawberry mix, then pudding mix.
Repeat layers.
Top with other half of Cool Whip.
Keep chilled until ready to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Poach chicken with celery, onion and bay leaf.
Remove bones and skin.
Line rectangular baking pan with meat.
Slice water chestnuts and mushrooms over chicken.
Mix soups, sour cream and 1 cup chicken stock.
Pour over chicken.
Prepare dressing with 1 cup stock.
Sprinkle over soup layer.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour.

title: sicilian salad
directions: In a bowl, combine beans, celery, onion and olives.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Combine oil, vinegar and lemon juice. Pour over bean mixture and stir to coat ingredients well. Refrigerate overnight.
Add tuna to salad and serve.

title: high octane baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot and cook endlessly.

title: potato souffl
directions: Mix first three ingredients well and pour into a buttered souffl dish.
Top with shredded cheddar.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Pour margarine or butter in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add rest of ingredients, one by one, on top of each other.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter, then nuts, chocolate chips and coconut and pour milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Allow to cool 15 minutes before cutting.

title: tacos
directions: In cooking oil, brown meat, onion and garlic until no longer pink.
Add other ingredients and cook over low heat for about 20 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburg and onion; drain. Add garlic, chili powder and 1/2 jar spaghetti sauce. Simmer 5 minutes.
Warm tortillas as directed on package. Divide meat into 10 parts.
Place a scoop of meat in each shell.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon cheese.
Roll up and place in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Pour other 1/2 jar sauce over top; sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
They freeze well.
Reheat in microwave.

title: white sangria
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir gently.
Add sugar to taste, if desired.
Serve in tall glasses with ice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Cut sausage into 1-inch pieces and remove skin.
In large pot, add oil and brown sausage.
Add tomato.
Cook for 45 minutes on low.
Stir occasionally.

title: summertime fruit salad
directions: Cube or scoop melons.
Mix with other fruit.
Pour the blend of sugar and juice over the top of the fruit.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Chicken Mixture:
Mix all ingredients except margarine and set aside.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Break cake into pieces (after cooled) into punch bowl.
Prepare vanilla pudding and pour over cake in bowl.
Layer pineapple, cherry pie filling and bananas. Cover with Cool Whip and top with pecans and cherries.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Gradually beat in vanilla and suagr.
Fold in chips and nuts.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop cookies by small teaspoonful on ungreased foil placed on cookie sheets.
Place in oven, close door, turn off oven.
Do not open door until next morning.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Spoon pie filling into
a
greased 9-inch square baking dish. Spoon pineapple over
pie
filling.
Sprinkle
cake mix evenly over fillings.
Drizzle
margarine over cake mix.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: white chocolate pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup skim milk until smooth.
Add remaining 1 1/2 cups of milk and pudding mix with vanilla. Stir in Cool Whip until smooth, then spoon into crust. Chill until set. Serves 8.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Beat oleo or butter in a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds. Add brown sugar and beat until well combined.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add the flour mixture to the beaten mixture. Beat at low speed just until combined.
Stir in chocolate pieces and 1 cup nuts.
Spread batter into pan.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sunday night potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes into small pieces.
Cook until tender.
(Usually I cook with very little water, as vitamins are in the water the potatoes are cooked in.)
Add milk, cheese, onion and salt and pepper to taste.
(I also use 1/2 teaspoon Tony Cachere Creole seasoning.)
Cut ham slices into small pieces and add this and the broccoli.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with crackers or ham sandwiches.
(We like our soup cheesy, so you can add to or take away cheese to your family's taste.)

title: cracker jacks
directions: Cook all ingredients together.
Bring to boil and cook 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Stir and pour over popcorn. Spread in pan (may take 2).
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 250°.
Stir every 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian fruit cake
directions: You will need a very large bowl to mix everything together. Shell and chop nuts.
Chop candied fruit coarsely.

Put fruit, raisins, and nuts in large bowl and add about cup of flour and toss to coat fruit to keep from sticking together when mixing. Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time alternating with flour and mixing well after each. Add flavorings.
When all other ingredients are mixed well, add fruit and nut mixture a little at a time, stirring in between until all is mixed well together. Batter will make two 3-layer cakes.
Pour in greased, floured pans and bake at 325 degrees for 40 minutes or until done.
Cool. Cover each layer with the following filling and stack 3 layers. Wrap second cake in foil and freeze for later.

title: beef cantoneese for crock-pot
directions: Brown beef cubes and drain off the fat.
Place in crock-pot. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on High for 1 hour, then turn down to low and cook for 6 hours.
Serve with rice or noodles. Great for a busy day.

title: marzetti
directions: Lightly brown pepper, onion, hamburger and sausage. Drain off grease.
Add all other ingredients except for cheese.
Mix and pour into a casserole dish. Top with cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. Can bake up to 45 minutes.

title: spiced cranberry-orange mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water in a large bowl. Stir in cranberry sauce, cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.
Stir in orange and walnuts.
Spoon into 5-cup mold.
Refrigerate about 4 hours or until firm.
Unmold.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 10 servings.

title: budget beef stroganoff
directions: Sprinkle meat with seasonings. Brown in butter. Stir in soup and add 1 cup broth. Cover and simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour. Add onions; cook 10 more minutes. Blend remaining broth and flour; stir into meat mixture. Cook about 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Add sour cream. Heat through but do not boil. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Let cool slightly. Roll in powdered sugar or coconut.

title: chicken piquant
directions: Place chicken pieces in Dutch oven.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, more to brown chicken and thicken sauce.
Serve with rice.
Serves 6.

title: dessert hard sauce
directions: Cream butter and sugar together and work in the flavoring. Serve cold with hot puddings or apple dumplings.

title: all-in-one casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown beef and drain.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with potatoes, carrots, peas, celery, onion and rice.
Combine soup and water.
Pour over all.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until the rice and vegetables are tender.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: carrot pecan cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, then set aside.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs together.
Add flour mixture slowly.
When all is mixed, stir in carrots and nuts, then raisins.
Pour into tube pan and bake for about 45 minutes.

title: chicken en casserole
directions: Remove skin from chicken breasts.
Place in skillet.
Add broth, wine and enough water to cover.
Bring to boil and simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Transfer with slotted spoon to casserole.
Boil down broth to 1/4 cup.
Mix together onion, mayonnaise, lemon juice, sugar, reduced broth and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cover with almonds and bake 10 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix beans in
crock-pot or baking dish.
Brown hamburger, bacon and onion
together
and
add
to bean mixture.
Mix catsup, brown sugar
and
mustard
together and pour over bean and meat mixture.
Bake in
oven for 1 1/2 hours or cook in crock-pot for 4 to 5 hours on high setting.

title: italian style steamed zucchini
directions: Heat olive oil and saute garlic.
Slice zucchini, green pepper and onion.
Add to garlic.
Add remaining seasoning and cook over low heat, stirring frequently.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Combine milk with almond and vanilla extracts; set aside.
In large bowl at high speed, cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Alternately add 1/4 cup flour with 1/3 cup milk mixture.
Place in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 40 minutes at 300° or until done.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly on rack.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Melt butter in 9 x 13 inch pan. Mix broccoli, cheese, Jiffy Cornbread mix, onion, eggs and milk. Pour in pan. Bake about 45 to 60 minutes, until done.

title: ice cream custard
directions: In a medium saucepan, beat together eggs, milk, sugar and salt.
Cook over a low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick enough to coat metal spoon and reaches at least 160°.
Cool quickly by setting pan in ice or cool water, stirring for few minutes. Add desired fruit.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled, at least 1 hour.
When ready to freeze, mix together chilled custard, whipping cream and vanilla.
Pour into a 1-gallon ice cream freezer can.
Freeze according to manufacturer's directions using 6 parts ice to 1 part rock salt. Transfer to freezer containers once freezing is completed.
Place in freezer until firm.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 quarts.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix together and roll into balls.
Mash with a fork.
Place pecan on each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: festive bean dip
directions: Warm and soften refried beans in pan with margarine and spices.
Spread in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Brown meat; add taco seasoning as directed. Layer meat mixture on top of refried beans. Sprinkle grated cheese on top of meat.
Place in oven until cheese just melts.
Remove.
Layer sour cream, salsa, lettuce and tomato over top.
Serve with tortilla chips.
(I like to stick the chips right into the dip.)

title: uncle mike's french toast
directions: Preheat griddle or frypan using vegetable spray or Crisco shortening.
Using medium bowl, beat 4 eggs with fork.
Add milk, vanilla extract and cinnamon and beat until combined.
Place 2 bread slices into mixture, coating both sides.
Place bread onto griddle.
When underside looks browned, turn.
Place 2 slices of cheese on one slice of bread and place remaining browned slice on top of cheese (making a sandwich).
Flip entire sandwich over until browned.
Continue with remaining slices.
Place on serving plate and top with strawberry preserves.
Serves 4.

title: snow ball(children's recipes)
directions: Make Jell-O as directed, except decrease water by 1 cup.
Pour into round-bottom bowl.
Let set in fridge.
Invert on a plate. Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Decorate for Christmas.

title: crab imperial
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and pour in baking dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Let the cream cheese and butter come to room temperature. In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and the cream cheese together. Add the sugar one cup at a time and make sure that it is well incorporated before you add each cup. Next, mix in the teaspoons of vanilla. Mix in one cup of cake flour and two eggs at a time. Again, make sure the cake flour and eggs are well incorporated before you add another cup and more eggs. Coat the bottom and sides of a pound cake pan very well with butter. Put the cake into a cold oven and then turn the oven to 350 degrees for 1 hour and 20-25 minutes. Remove cake from oven. Let it sit for 30 minutes and then transfer the cake to
a cake plate. Eat it plain or with fruit and whipped cream.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend only until smooth. Chill and serve.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients and add butter, egg and vanilla. Mix well; drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the sugar and milk.
Sift 1/2 of the flour, salt and baking powder together. Add to the egg mixture. Beat the batter with mixer until smooth, adding as much flour as needed. Batter should be thin enough to pour.
Pour 1/4 cup through funnel into hot oil in a lattice fashion.
Oil should be about 3/4-inch deep and about 375°.
Brown on one side. Turn. Cooking time is about 1 to 2 minutes.

title: tiaramisu
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar.
Add liquor and cheese.
Mix well. Fold in beaten whites.
Dip ladyfingers in coffee (do not soak). Line bottom of bowl and sides with ladyfingers.
Top with half of cheese mixture.
Add more ladyfingers and rest of cheese. Dust top with cocoa using sifter.
Chill several hours.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: In a heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate.
In another pan, heat whipping cream to scalding. Slowly add to melted chocolate.
Place pan in bowl of ice water until cool and thickened, stirring frequently. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper; coat hands with cocoa and form chocolate into balls.
Serve well chilled.
Makes about 30.

title: country fried catfish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pat dry 4 catfish fillets.
Coat catfish on both sides with cornmeal mixture.
Fry at 350° in hot oil until golden brown (about 5 to 6 minutes).

title: fudge brownie fingers
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar and stir.
Add melted butter and chocolate.
Mix flour, salt and nuts and add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla and stir until well blended, but do not beat.
Pour into a well buttered 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325°
for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in 2-inch fingers.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cheese custard
directions: Mix in order given and pour in large 10-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake until custard is firm.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs good, then add sugar and the rest of the ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 275° for 15 minutes, then at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.
(Top of cookie will look pale.)

title: mom's homemade jelly
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; blend well.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring frequently, until thickened.
Combine fruit and juice flavors as desired.
Great on pancakes, sandwiches and toast.

title: italian chocolate ice cream
directions: Melt 3 squares unsweetened chocolate in top of 2-quart double boiler over simmering water.
Stir in condensed milk until smooth. Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Beat egg yolks in medium bowl until thick and lemon colored; stir in melted chocolate mixture gradually.
Heat sugar, half and half, coffee and 2 squares semi-sweet chocolate in top of 2-quart double boiler over simmering water until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat; stir in rum and creme de cacao.
Mix chocolate mixtures, cream and grated chocolate.
Freeze in ice cream maker according to manufacturer's directions.
(I add 1 cup half and half and 1 cup milk to final mix since recipe is such a strong chocolate mixture.)

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Let brown over low heat. Do not scorch.
Mix eggs and milk together.
Pour into butter and sugar mixture.
Keep stirring until all melts.
Add remaining sugar and enough flour to thicken.
Cook until thick.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake.
Makes 2 pies.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together.
Add lemon juice. Take strawberries and put in juice (do that while you have a full bowl).
Put one layer of graham crackers and layer of filling until full.

title: microwave baked apples
directions: Peel and core apples.
Slice or cut into rings.
Place in microwave-safe 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Place remaining ingredients in dish.
Bake, uncovered, in microwave 3 to 5 minutes or until apples are tender.
(May vary with various microwaves.) Serve.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with any fresh vegetables (carrots, celery, tomatoes, cauliflower, etc.).

title: tomatoes country style
directions: Beat together with a mixer, garlic, parsley, salt and cream cheese; add basil.
Cut tomatoes into 12 even slices, about 1/2 inch thick.
Spread 6 slices with about 2 tablespoons of cream cheese mixture each.
Top with remaining slices to make 6 sandwiches.
Dip each in flour, then in egg mixture; finally dip in bread crumbs.
Fry on both sides over medium heat in mixture of butter and olive oil until brown.
Garnish with fresh basil or parsley, if desired.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Brown ground beef and diced onions. Drain. Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam cooking spray. Transfer drained ground beef and onions into baking dish and spread evenly over bottom of dish. Layer sliced potatoes over ground beef and onions. Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over potatoes. In separate bowl, mix golden mushroom soup and water. Blend thoroughly. Pour soup mixture over cheese layer. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter an oblong casserole.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix and 1 cup rice.
Place chicken pieces in casserole, fat side down. Mix cream of chicken soup with 1 3/4 cans water; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until chicken is done.
Stir from bottom before serving.

title: apricot pound cake
directions: Mix the items.
Bake at 350° until cake springs back.

title: pecan dip
directions: Heat butter and garlic salt.
Combine with cream cheese and milk.
Stir in seasoning and beef.
Fold in sour cream.
Mix in pecans.
Great with Carr crackers!

title: watergate salad
directions: Make pudding as suggested on package.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Keep in refrigerator until served.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in hot milk. Mash well. Separately beat eggs with sugar and salt. Add bread and milk to egg mixture. Add vanilla and butter. Bake in a greased pan or dish at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean. Add raisins on top. Serve with whipped cream or Dream Whip.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl except eggs.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat at high rate of speed for 2 minutes.
Grease tube pan good and pour in batter.
Bake about an hour at 325° or until done.
Let cool in pan 25 minutes before dumping.

title: macaroon salad
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add egg, margarine and vanilla.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan and bake this mixture 30 minutes at 350° or until light golden brown.
Don't overbake.
Cool and crumble. In large glass bowl layer Cool Whip, bananas, crumbs and nuts; end with Cool Whip.
Be sure top layer covers bananas so they won't turn brown.
Sprinkle a few crumbs on top and refrigerate 4 hours. Good!
We like this all year round!

title: chocolate caramel nut bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Combine remaining milk, cake mix and oleo; mix well. Press half of cake mixture into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup nuts and chocolate chips over crust; top with caramel mixture, spreading to edges of pan.
Top with teaspoonfuls of remaining nuts, pressing lightly into top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly. Refrigerate.
Cut into bars to serve.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: kole daumer(meat wrapped in cabbage leaves)
directions: Steam cabbage just until the leaves are pliable. Mix other ingredients together. Wrap small amounts of mixed ingredients in a cabbage leaf. Bake at 350° in shallow baking dish with a small amount of water until done, about 1 1/2 hours. Baste frequently and dot with butter before serving.

title: grandma's rice pudding
directions: Mix together.
Turn into 10 x 10 x 3-inch well-greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until crust forms on top.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute hamburger meat, onion and green peppers until meat is browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer until rice is done.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, salt, corn syrup and chocolate.
Add milk.
Cook rapidly, stirring constantly.
Cook until it will form soft ball in water.
Cool until hand can be held at bottom of pan.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy.
Add nuts, if desired.
Put in greased pan or dish and cut in squares.
Can use peanut butter by using 1/3 cup peanut butter rather than nuts.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown first three ingredients together; drain and rinse.
Put in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir occasionally. Serve with jalapeno peppers.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Boil water; stir in grits.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add butter, eggs, salt, Tabasco and pepper.
Combine grits mixture with grated cheese.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: maple peach jam
directions: Chop the peaches finely.
In a non-aluminum pot, combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil gently and stir frequently until thick.
It's ready when it holds its shape when dropped on a cold plate.
If problem thickening, add finely chopped apple for pectin and boil longer.
Ladle hot jam into sterilized jars, leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath or 5 minutes in pressure canner with vent open.
Begin timing when steam comes out in a steady stream.

title: party peas
directions: Cook peas in salted water.
Add peas to white sauce.
Add chopped boiled eggs and mushrooms.
Place in baking dish; spread with crushed cracker crumbs.
Bake in 325° to 350° oven until brown.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In large bowl, put bite size lettuce, layer of chopped green peppers, uncooked frozen green peas, chopped green onions. Top with a layer of mayo, with a sprinkling of sugar over mayo. Sprinkle crispy fried (crumpled) bacon over mayo, then top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Best if sets for several hours.

title: rhubarb krisp
directions: Combine rhubarb with 1/2 cup white sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 2 tablespoons flour.
Pour mixture into a deep 8-inch pan and dot with margarine.

title: chocolate cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Stir in water, oil, white vinegar and vanilla.
Beat well and fill baking cups 1/3 full.
Combine cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Beat well.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Top each cupcake with a teaspoonful of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with sugar and nuts (if desired).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for regular size cupcakes or 12 to 15 minutes for mini size cakes.
Cool at least 4 hours.
This is essential.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen regular size and about 6 dozen mini size.

title: butter beans and peas
directions: In pot, cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender.

title: tortoni
directions: Combine marshmallows and sherry and heat on low until marshmallows melt, stirring occasionally.
Cool for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.

title: stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry vegetables with oil until tender.
Add 4 tablespoons water and steam while you mix the onion gravy with the 1 3/4 cups water in a saucepan until thick.
Add to the vegetables and mix. Serve over rice.

title: plantation crunch
directions: Melt candibark and peanut butter. Stir until smooth. Add peanuts and rice krispies. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: fruit salad
directions: Chill peaches and pineapple tidbits.
When chilled, slice bananas into fruit.
Stir in vanilla pudding mix.
Easy and good.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Add spaghetti sauce mix and tomato
sauce.
Simmer
gently
to
let
flavors combine. Spread meat
mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer the Mozzarella cheese and sour cream on top of meat.
Put crescent rolls
on top and brush with melted butter.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 375°. Serves 8 to 10.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Season to taste.
Add soup.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes more, until done.
Serve over cooked rice or large buns.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter and both sugars. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda. Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Roll into balls and place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 112 cookies.
Recipe may be halved.

title: mexican white cheese dip
directions: Microwave until melted.
May add additional milk to thin as needed.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the zucchini, pecans, raisins and lemon juice.
Set aside. Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and beat.
Fold in zucchini mixture.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cheddar beef pie
directions: Combine meat, egg, onion, 3/4 cup corn flake crumbs, barbecue sauce and seasonings; mix lightly.
Press meat mixture onto bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Bate at 400° for 15 minutes. Remove meat shells from oven; drain.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Saute celery slices in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Combine celery, cheese and mushrooms.
Toss lightly; spoon into hot meat shell.
Melt remaining margarine and combine with 1/4 cup crumbs; sprinkle over cheese mixture.
Return to oven; continue baking 10 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrots in butter for 10 minutes.
Add flour to mixture.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add broth and half and half until thickened.
Stir in salt, pepper, peas, and chopped chicken.
Pour chicken mixture into shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with pastry.
Cut slits to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Serves 5 people.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chile beer pot roast
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
In Dutch oven, brown meat. Combine undrained tomatoes, undrained chile peppers, 1/2 cup beer, chili powder and bouillon.
Pour over meat.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat to ovenproof platter.
Keep warm.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Combine in order given.
Mix well and pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and let set in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.

title: raisin pie
directions: Put some hot water on raisins and let them set for about 15 minutes; drain.
Mix ingredients.
Pour into unbaked deep dish pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: cheezy broccoli casserole(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Cook broccoli in package for 3 to 4 minutes; set aside. Combine rice, soup, milk, Cheez Whiz, salt and pepper in a 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave for 2 to 4 minutes, until cheese melts and can be easily blended.
Add onion, celery, broccoli and water chestnuts to cheese-rice mixture; stir thoroughly.
Cook for 12 to 14 minutes, rotating dish after 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Put veggies in a large kettle and cover with one quart water. Simmer until tender.
Mix milk with 1 quart cool water in blender; add to veggies.
Make a roux of 1/2 cup melted butter or margarine and enough flour to make a smooth paste.
Add to soup.
Add grated cheese to taste.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot.

title: ice cream float
directions: Use tall glasses.
Put several tablespoons of ice cream (vanilla or your choice) into glasses.
Pour Coke over ice cream. Stir slowly, then enjoy.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Crumb as for pie crust.
Take 2 eggs in cup, beat well.
Fill cup with milk to make 1 cup.
Pour into batter.
Spread real thin on greased cookie sheet.
Spread with filling, cover filling with crust top dough.
Add sugar and cornstarch to your fruit.

title: microwaved gingered chicken
directions: Arrange meat, skin side up, thickest pieces to outside in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch dish.
I use Reynolds cooking bags.
Mix remaining ingredients, except cornstarch and water.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes, rotate 1/2 turn, 10 to 15 minutes more on High, until thickest are done.

title: hearty tortellini soup
directions: Saute onion, celery, carrots and garlic in melted margarine until tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach, do not cook.
Mix all ingredients together (except bread) and chill overnight.
Hollow out center of bread to make a bowl.
Break hollowed out bread into small pieces.
Place dip in bread bowl and place broken pieces around to use for dipping.
Also may use crackers of your choice.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together in 1 1/2 quart casserole dish the sugar and white corn syrup.
Microwave at High for 4 minutes.
Stir in roasted salted peanuts.
Microwave at High for 3 to 5 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla, blending well.
Microwave at High 1 to 2 minutes (until peanuts are light brown).
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet or nonstick sheet.
Cool for 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in oblong baking dish.
Pour in rice over the butter.
Lay salted chicken (I don't salt) over top of rice.
If you use long grain and wild, sprinkle dry mix over chicken now. Pour chicken soup over chicken and add water.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: polish reuben casserole
directions: Place sauerkraut in strainer in sink; rinse with cold water. Press to drain well. Combine onion, soup, milk and mustard in bowl; blend well. Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Spread sauerkraut in prepared pan; top with uncooked noodles. Spoon soup mixture evenly over noodles. Top with sausage and cheese. Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle over top of casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until noodles are tender. Serve with warm buns.

title: sweet sour broccoli and cauliflower
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower until tender-crisp.
Turn into a warm serving dish. While vegetables cook, fry bacon until crisp. Remove bacon and reserve.
Save 3 tablespoons of the bacon drippings.
Add onions.
Saute for 2 minutes, then stir in brown sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Heat.
Pour sauce over cauliflower and broccoli in serving dish.
Top with bacon.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: lucille's raspberry dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O and water and let set slightly. Mix remaining ingredients and fold into Jell-O mixture.
Whip Dream Whip as soon as Jell-O is made.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in strips.
Brown in oil.
Add tomato juice and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer until liquid is almost gone.
Add soup and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and simmer 10 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: candied fruit peel
directions: With sharp knife cut through the peel only around the middle of fruit and again around at cross angles.
Remove peel quarters and slice into 1/4-inch sticks.
Cover peel with cold water, bring to a boil and cook for 20 minutes.
Drain and repeat process, drain again.
Combine syrup, sugar and hot water.
Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Add peel and cook to 230°.
Peel becomes transparent and most of sugar is absorbed.
Remove peel with slotted spoon.
Press against side of pan to remove excess syrup. Put strips on foil or cookie sheet.
Separate.
When cool and slightly dried, toss in granulated sugar to coat.
Also, may use 4 to 6 oranges, but save 1 cup of cooking water for the 1 cup hot water.
Lemon peel can also be candied in this way.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Cook 2 to 3 minutes the brown sugar, egg, milk and oleo. Remove from heat and add pecans, coconut, graham cracker crumbs and vanilla.
Place whole graham crackers on cookie sheet and spread with filling.
Top with a layer of graham crackers.
(You can make another layer of filling and crackers if you prefer.)

title: chicken log
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, steak sauce and curry powder; beat with mixer until smooth.
Stir in chicken, celery and parsley.
Shape into 9-inch long log; wrap in waxed paper.
Chill for 4 to 5 hours.
Roll log in almonds.
Serve with crackers. Makes 1 (9-inch) log.
Nice use for leftover chicken.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Combine avocados, mayonnaise and lemon juice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix cooked squash, soup, onion, cheese, beaten eggs, salt and pepper and cracker crumbs.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with additional crushed crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: deviled pecan spread(makes 2 cups)
directions: In bowl, blend deviled ham and cream cheese.
Stir in pineapple, green pepper and onion.
Chill at least 4 hours or overnight.
Mound mixture on serving plate; garnish with pecans and parsley.
Serve as spread on Ritz crackers.
(May be refrigerated up to 2 days.)

title: chocolate bundt cake
directions: Mix all and pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Beat shortening, butter, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Sift together the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Roll into balls approximately 1-inch in diameter.
Roll the balls in a mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine and sugar, add and mix remainder of wet ingredients.
Add and mix all dry ingredients except chocolate chips.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and cranberry sauce.
Chill until thickened slightly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 4 cup mold.
Chill until firm. If you double recipe, use only 1 cup (total) pineapple juice.

title: glenn's japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until set.
No one can make a mistake on this pie, not even a man.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Cover the first 3 ingredients with cold water for 3 hours. Rinse and drain well.
Mix the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Cool.
Place cucumbers in containers.
Pour solution over them, seal and freeze.
Either bags or freezer boxes will do.

title: dream cream
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, evaporated milk, sweetened condensed milk, gelatin and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour into freezer can of a 1 1/2 to 2-gallon hand-turned or electric freezer.
Add enough milk to fill can about 3/4 full.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Let ripen at least 2 hours.
Yields 1 1/2 gallons.

title: marshmallow candy
directions: Soak gelatine in half the water.
Put remaining water and the sugar in saucepan and bring to boil.
Continue boiling until syrup will string and thread when dropped from tip of spoon.
When mixture reaches this soft ball stage, pour into mixing bowl and add gelatine.
Let cool to warm and then add vanilla.

title: angel food jello cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve strawberry Jell-O in 2 cups of hot water.
Pour largest package (16 ounce) of frozen strawberries into hot Jell-O.
Place angel food cake upside down into Jell-O and push it down until soaked.
Then seal the bowl.
Can be served with Cool Whip.

title: fiesta chicken and rice bake
directions: Mix soup, salsa, water, corn, and rice in 2 qt. shallow baking dish. Top with chicken and sprinkle with paprika. Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done. Sprinkle with cheese. Serves 4.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat first four ingredients together well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and pour into a pan.
Bake in moderate oven, 325°, for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: irish skillet bread
directions: Combine biscuit mix, sugar, raisins and spices. Add liquid ingredients.
Stir lightly.
Bake in 8-inch greased ovenproof skillet at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: ham with pineapple sauce
directions: Prepare ham according to package in medium saucepan.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and cornstarch together.
Stir in pineapple, lemon juice and mustard.
Bring mixture to boil, stirring, and cook until thickened (about 2 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Spoon over sliced ham and serve.

title: chicken 'n' rice
directions: Place each piece of chicken on a separate sheet of aluminum foil.
Divide the rice evenly on top of each piece of chicken. Sprinkle the dry soup on top of the rice.
Place a pat of butter on top.
Close the aluminum foil tightly.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in the shortening.
In a separate bowl, beat together the egg, vinegar and water.
With a fork, add the liquid to the flour mixture until it holds together.
Yields a 2 crust 9-inch pie shell.

title: shrimp and seafood gumbo
directions: Roux:
Put oil in heavy iron pot over medium heat.
When oil is hot, stir in flour gradually.
Lower heat.
It is essential you stir constantly.
Stir, stir, stir until flour is golden brown. Do this over low heat.
Do not try to hurry it up.
Keep stirring after done or it will scorch.

title: cheese soup
directions: Dissolve the 6 bouillon cubes in the 4 cups water.
To broth, add the chopped onions, celery and diced potatoes (precook these 3 ingredients before adding to broth).
Next, precook California blend vegetables for 10 minutes and add to broth.
Add cream of chicken and celery soup and the 1 1/2 cans of water.
Stir; heat through.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Do not make in crock-pot, but can be kept hot in one.
This soup freezes well.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, soup, onions, sour cream, carrots, pimento and 1/2 package herb stuffing mix.
Melt butter and stir in remainder of herb stuffing mix.
Line dish with stuffing crumb mixture holding back part of crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Bake about 30 minutes at 325°.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Place 2 packages strawberries in blender.
Blend until smooth. Combine berries and grape juice in punch bowl.
Add remaining berries to float in punch.
Add club soda just before serving. (Pour carefully to preserve fizz.)

title: congealed tuna salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in a saucepan.
Let stand 1 minute.
Cook over low heat, stirring until gelatin dissolves. Combine remaining ingredients; stir in gelatin mixture.
Pour into a lightly oiled 6-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold salad on lettuce leaves, if desired.
Yield 6 servings.

title: onion pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Into bowl, sift flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in butter and half the shortening until mixture is very fine.
Cut in remaining shortening until particles are the size of peas.
Sprinkle milk, about a tablespoon at a time, over mixture, stirring with fork until dough clings together and cleans the bowl.
Shape dough into a smooth ball.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper.
Combine soup and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave coconut pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk together in a 2-quart microwavable dish.
Cook for eight minutes.
Stir frequently.
Add well beaten eggs; cook 2 minutes longer.
Stir often.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into one baked pastry pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake until brown.

title: lo-cal waffles
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add flour, salt and baking powder; add milk and mix gently.
Pour in preheated waffle iron and bake until brown.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix and pour into crust.
Chill in refrigerator for about 4 hours.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Heat cider and ginger ale together with red hots and spices. Simmer but do not boil.
Pour over orange slices in mugs.

title: hot chocolate mix #1
directions: Combine all ingredients.
To serve, mix 1/3 cup mix with hot water or milk.
Add marshmallows.
Makes 80 ounces.
Makes great gifts in Mason jars.

title: grillades
directions: Cut veal round into serving size pieces.
Heat shortening in 10-inch skillet.
Add veal and brown on both sides.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Brown flour in same shortening.
Add onion and saute slightly.
Stir in tomatoes, green pepper, parsley, garlic, thyme, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Place meat in pan.
Pour in enough water to cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve over grits.
Serves 4.

title: guacamole 2
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well. Cover and chill thoroughly. Yields 2 cups. Place the avocado pits in the guacamole until ready to serve. (prevents it from turning color)

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Clean and remove outside skin of broccoli stems.
Boil in salted water until firm-tender (about 7 minutes).
Rinse under cold water until cooled; let drain well.
Cut bacon into thin strips and saute until crisp; drain and cool.
Dice celery and green onions fine.
Dice tomatoes small.
Cut broccoli in bite size; mix with celery, onions and bacon.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough mayonnaise to coat well.
Make a few hours ahead of time and refrigerate to blend flavors.

title: brisket
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put half solution on bottom of brisket and other half on top.
Cover with foil; bake at 300° to 325° at least 3 hours.

title: macaroni goulash
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender. Meanwhile, prepare the following sauce of other ingredients:
Melt butter in heavy skillet, then saute onion, green pepper, celery and hamburger in it.
Separate meat into small pieces.
When meat is browned and onion tender, add seasonings and chili powder.
Add the tomato sauce, mixing well; sprinkle with cheese and allow to simmer about 15 minutes.
When macaroni is tender, blanch in hot water; add to simmering sauce and cover for a few minutes longer. Serves 4.

title: oven baked french fries
directions: Cut potatoes into lengthwise strips; brush with egg whites. Sprinkle with cheese and oregano, if desired.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes on sheet prepared with vegetable cooking spray.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt almond bark and peanut butter. Put on wax paper in pan. Melt chips and swirl on top of almond bark and peanut butter. Refrigerate until set up.

title: oven baked potatoes(serves 8)
directions: Mix together hash browns, cream of chicken soup, sour cream, cheese, onions, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup melted butter. Spread mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine the remaining melted butter and crushed cornflakes and top mixture evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburger; do not drain. Add water and season to taste with spices. Cook 30 minutes.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat; cool.
Add marshmallows and nuts to chocolate mixture.
Shape into 2 rolls 1 1/2 to 2 inches in diameter; roll each in coconut.
Refrigerate. When rolls are thoroughly chilled, slice into 1/2-inch slices. Yields about 3 dozen.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Stew hen; remove meat from bones and cut into pieces.
Return to pot and add tomato soup, tomatoes, onion, lima beans, potatoes and seasonings.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add corn and butter.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
If desired, thicken slightly with flour mixed with cold water.
Season to taste.

title: lisa's meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, pork, 1/2 can tomato sauce, chopped green peppers, carrot, Rice Krispies and minced onion in a large casserole dish.
Once mixed, shape into a loaf.
Pour remaining tomato sauce on top of loaf.
Fill tomato can with water and pour around meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pork sausage and vegetable hot dish
directions: Fry pork sausage.
When done, cut into 2-inch pieces.
Set aside.
Slice potatoes and fry in butter.
Salt.
Warm corn and beans in pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Serve hot.
Add pepper to taste.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Cut pineapple rings into pieces.
Add oranges, marshmallows and sour cream.
Mix well.
Pile on serving plate.
Sprinkle with coconut and top with cherry halves. Refrigerate.

title: baked onions
directions: Slice up onions.
Put in cold water.
Bring to a boil.
Just when it starts to boil, drain them.
Repeat the step; cover onions in cold water and bring to a boil.
Drain.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Dab with butter.
Salt and pepper to taste, then slice Velveeta to cover onions.
Take 10 or so Ritz crackers and crumble over the top of the Velveeta.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, just enough to melt cheese.

title: party white cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: hot sausage bites
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium bowl, combine ingredients and mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Place 1-inch apart on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove from baking sheets immediately. Serve hot.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, milk and salt.
Mix well, then add corn.
Put in an 8-inch square buttered dish.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
(May be doubled; use a 13 x 9-inch dish!)

title: french rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Saute oleo, onion and bell pepper, but do not brown. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Place in baking dish and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: apple puffs
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Add oil, milk and egg.
Mix well with fork.
Stir in apples.
Drop by teaspoon into 375° fat.
Fry 3 minutes until golden brown.
Roll warm puffs in cinnamon-sugar mixture.

title: sante fe potato salad
directions: In large saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling water to cover until tender, about 40 minutes; drain.
Cool slightly; cut into cubes.

title: beef-taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Drain.
Stir in kidney beans with liquid, tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Heat to boiling.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in greased casserole, top with chips.
Put remaining mixture over layer, add cheese over top. Cover and cook at 350 degrees for 25 - 30 minutes.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: homemade bologna
directions: Mix together like a meat loaf; marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: mrs. bertie's lemon cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and apricot nectar.
Beat until smooth.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 30 minutes.
Combine confectioners sugar and lemon juice until of glaze consistency.
Glaze thoroughly cooled cake.

title: chili
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil. Add beef and cook until brown. Drain and stir in tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes, steak sauce, chili powder and cumin. Heat to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in beans and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Ladle into bowls and top with shredded cheese.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and mix well.
The more it is mixed the better it will be.
Put in pan and round it. Cover with catsup.
Cook for 30 minutes or until done.

title: rarebit
directions: Put milk on to heat.
Make a paste of mustard and flour. Combine with well beaten egg.
Add to milk.
Add cheese and when mixture begins to thicken, stir in rolled crackers and salt and pepper.
Serve on crisp crackers.
Dust with paprika.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Bring water to boil with bouillon cubes.
Add carrots and celery.
Bring to boil (about 5 minutes).
Add remaining vegetables.
Bring to boil.
Simmer until all vegetables are tender.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Cube Velveeta; add and stir until melted.

title: garden saute
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion, bell pepper and garlic. Stir-fry 2 minutes. Add squash; stir-fry 3 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Add tomato, basil and lemon pepper. Cook 1 minute or until thoroughly heated. Remove from heat.
Sprinkle with cheese.
May serve with pasta for a main dish.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix brown and white sugar.
Add flour and mix.
Beat 2 eggs and add milk or cream.
Melt butter and add to egg and milk mixture.
Pour this into sugar and flour mixture.
Mix well and add vanilla and pecans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage; drain and set aside. Preheat oven to 425°. Press crust into lightly greased 14-inch pizza pan, forming a 1/2-inch rim. Bake 5 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook in big pot.
Melt sugar and syrup.
Add wax, then peanuts approximately 10 minutes after starting to boil or when peanuts are done.
Remove from heat.
Add soda, stir well and pour into greased pan.
Spread thin.
Cool and crack.

title: coffee cake muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside. Sift dry ingredients into bowl. Cut in shortening to resemble coarse crumbs. Combine egg and milk; add all at once to flour mixture. Stir just until moistened. Line muffin tins with paper cups. Spoon in small amount of batter. Top with layer of nut mixture. Repeat layers, filling pans 2/3 full. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican beans
directions: Microwave:
Combine first 3 ingredients in a 2-quart microwavable casserole; cover.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes or until heated through.
Stir.
Top with cheese.
If desired, garnish with sour cream and green onion.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple delite cake
directions: Bake cake and cool.
Beat cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and 1 cup powdered sugar.
Add enough milk to make spreadable.
Set aside.
Mix undrained pineapple and the lemon pudding.
When cake is cooled, spread with the cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate overnight.

title: eggplant au gratin
directions: Peel eggplants.
Boil in salted water until tender.
Strain off water and mash.
Saute chopped onions in butter.
Beat eggs. Grate cheese.
Combine ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven 45 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and marinate for 24 hours or overnight. Add the remaining ingredients.

title: sugar and spice popcorn
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add sugar and spices.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Drizzle over popcorn and toss to mix well. Makes 2 quarts.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, stir together first five ingredients. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens (about 3 to 4 minutes). Gradually stir in cheese.
Add macaroni and tuna, mixing thoroughly.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over the top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: overnight pecan rolls
directions: Arrange frozen roll dough in greased bundt pan; drizzle with melted margarine.
Mix pudding mix, brown sugar, pecans, cinnamon in a small bowl.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Let rise, covered, all night.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake rolls for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Invert onto serving plate while warm.

title: beth's original chocolate maple fudge(1965)
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except vanilla.
Add vanilla last when candy is done.
Cook slowly until small amount tested in saucer is very firm.
(Firm enough to cut into blocks).
Beat well and pour on a platter.
Let cool and cut into blocks.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place hash browns and all but last two ingredients in 9 x 12-inch container.
Top with margarine and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop into hot fat, 1/4-inch deep until lightly browned on both sides.

title: saltine cracker cake
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar as for angel food cake. Add sugar, nuts and crackers.
Add to egg white mixture.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Prepare Dream Whip.
Put on cake.
Add pineapple on top of Dream Whip. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: rugalach
directions: Mix first three ingredients to make dough, then combine and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out in confectioners sugar.
Roll dough into 9-inch circles (6) and cut into triangles (16).
Brush with melted butter.
Spoon filling onto dough and roll from wide to narrow end.
Brush tops with beaten egg yolk.
Bake in 350° oven on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cake:
Put first 5 ingredients into a 13 x 9 pan and mix together well.
Place into a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cake will be a golden brown.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine and mix all ingredients and pour into cake pan.

title: fish creole
directions: In skillet cook onion, green pepper and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add undrained tomatoes (cut up), parsley flakes, bouillon granules and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Blend together cornstarch and water.
Stir into tomato mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cut fish into 1-inch pieces.
Add to tomato mixture, stirring to coat.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 5 to 7 minutes. Serve fish mixture over rice.

title: veal and mushroom stew(4 to 6 servings)
directions: Brown and cut up 4 cooked cubed veal patties.
Put them in the water.
Bring water to a boil.
Add bouillon cubes.
Cook until soft the onion, green pepper, potatoes, carrots, black pepper, curry powder, basil and garlic (about 10 to 15 minutes).
Add tomatoes, cream of mushroom soup and mushrooms (use the liquid in the cans).
Warm up.
Do not boil.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder. Then add butter, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 425° in muffin or corn stick rings until done.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and soda. Some flour can be added to the cranberries to prevent them from bleeding while baking. Add sugar, salt and egg. In a separate measuring cup, combine orange juice, butter and hot water to make 3/4 cup. Fold liquid into dry ingredients, then add cranberries and nuts. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Check with toothpick to see if done.

title: congo bar
directions: Melt margarine. Add sugar, peanut butter and eggs.
Mix with spoon.
Add rest of ingredients, ending with chocolate chips. Bake at 325°.
Leave soft like brownies in the middle.
Don't overbake.
Frost with chocolate icing.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil together.
Add zucchini and vanilla. Mix remaining ingredients together and add to zucchini mixture until blended.
Bake in a greased and sugared loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle the top with a little sugar, if desired.

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and salt until mixture is lemon colored.
Add butter and flour, then blend well.
Add milk and fold in 1 cup of coconut.
Pour into pie shells.
Top with remaining coconut.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and pour off grease.
Add onion, garlic, celery and green pepper to sausage and simmer until tender.
Wash rice and put all ingredients in a large bowl and mix thoroughly.
Then transfer all ingredients to Pyrex dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg; add to dry mixture.
Add hot water to mixture.
Heat oil to a rolling boil.
Drop mixture into boil by spoonfuls.
They will float to the top of oil; turn over and let brown.
Remove from oil and drain on paper towel.

title: swedish spice cake
directions: Butter tube pan and sprinkle with bread crumbs and shake out excess and set pan aside.
Sift and mix flour, soda, salt, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and cardamom.
Cream and mix sugar, oleo, vanilla, eggs and sour cream.
Mix above alternately beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Spoon batter into pan and bake about 1 hour in 325° oven.
Cake is done if knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs; add brown sugar, cinnamon, ginger and salt.
Mix well, then add milk and pumpkin.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: precious chicken
directions: Line casserole dish with chipped beef.
Slice chicken breast into as many small pieces as possible.
Mash each piece flat. Roll each piece of chicken breast with slice of chipped beef inside.
Roll slice of bacon around chicken and skewer with toothpick.
Place chicken rolls on chipped beef in dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Bake in oven for 2 hours.
Do not salt (beef is salty).
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Saute onions until golden.
Add flour, salt and pepper to onions.
Mix well.
Gradually add cream and chicken broth, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Add cooked rice to sauce, chicken, parsley and almonds.
Mix well and pour into a greased casserole.
Bake in a 425° oven for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off green peppers.
Remove seeds and membranes. Precook pepper cups in small amount of boiling water, salted, for 5 minutes.
Drain; sprinkle inside with salt.
Combine the next 4 ingredients.
Add Tabasco sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Fill peppers.
Place upright in oblong baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce around peppers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spoon tomato sauce over peppers when serving.

title: jack's hush puppies
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, salt, baking powder, onion, egg, milk, water and bacon drippings together and drop by teaspoonsful into hot deep fat.
Cook until golden.

title: brunch pie(good for any meal)
directions: Coat a 9-inch pie plate with margarine.
Mix hash and 1 beaten egg; press into plate to form crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Saute onion in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Layer cheese, sauteed onion and vegetables in crust.
Beat together remaining eggs, evaporated milk, flour, mustard, garlic powder and pepper.
Pour over mixture in crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until filling is set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream together butter and Crisco. Beat in slowly 3 cups sugar and eggs (1 at a time), beating well after each addition. Add flour alternately with milk, starting with flour and ending with flour. Add flavoring and fold in black walnuts, chopped (if desired). Put into 10-inch type pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours. Do not open door for 1 hour (sometimes 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours).

title: chicken surprise(i'm surprised i found it)
directions: Pour rice in buttered oblong baking dish.
(Do not use quick rice.)
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over the rice.
Place chicken pieces skin side up over rice and onion mixture.
Mix together mushroom soup with water and pour over chicken.
Prepare in advance; set automatic oven at 350° and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Roll crackers fine and mix with sugar and melted butter. Press in bottom and on sides of pie plate to make shell.
Bake in moderate oven for 5 minutes before filling.

title: marinated artichokes
directions: Cook artichokes as directed on package omitting salt; drain. Place artichokes in a shallow dish.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Makes 1 gallon or about 25 punch cups.

title: swedish oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg, then add all dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal last.
(You may have to work the oatmeal in with your hands.
It becomes very stiff.)
Try to blend as best you can.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in cold water.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Sift powdered sugar on top of cookies.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Place on plate to cool.
Store in Tupperware or in refrigerator in tight container.

title: big batch cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Blend in vanilla. Sift together soda, salt and flour.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chips, M&M's or raisins, whichever you choose.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased or sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: tomato soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pot and cook on medium heat. Do not let boil because of the cream.
Sprinkle parmesan on top.

title: e. z. easy cake squares
directions: Mix thoroughly 1 box of cake mix.
Add 1 egg and 1 stick of softened margarine.
Put in pan, 13 x 9-inch.
Pat around all of pan.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and top it with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat oil and saute pepper, onion, celery and garlic.
Add tomatoes, water and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and simmer 15 minutes more.
Add cornstarch.
Serve on rice.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in a heavy kettle, drain.
Add all the ingredients except the green beans, corn and macaroni.
Bring to a boil. Lower heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, bring to a boil and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: cheese ring with strawberry jam
directions: Combine and place in a 5 or 6-cup greased ring mold. Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Unmold and fill center with strawberry preserves.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, hot sauce and onion in a mixing bowl.
Mix egg and milk, leaving the dough stiff enough to spoon or roll in long rolls.
Fry in fish grease.
Brown slowly.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: easy italian sauce and pasta shells
directions: Cook the pasta according to package directions.
Saute the onion in the olive oil until softened (about 5 minutes).
If more liquid is needed, add the water.
Add the crushed tomatoes and the basil.
Mix well and cook, uncovered, on medium until the liquid is reduced.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook meats.
Add rest.
Serve with French bread and salad. Serves 10.

title: almond slaw
directions: Crush Oriental noodles, while still in package. Toast almonds in microwave for 1 to 2 minutes (or until almonds are crunchy). Mix cabbage, noodles and almonds. Mix oil, vinegar and Oriental seasoning packet in a small bowl. Keep oil/vinegar/seasoning mixture separate from cabbage mixture until just prior to serving. Serves about 3 to 4 people.

title: eight hour brandy cheesecake
