directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and brandy until very smooth with electric mixer.
Add eggs; beat just enough to mix in. Grease and flour 2-quart souffle dish (or large spring-form pan). Fill with mixture.
Place in a shallow pan of water.
Bake in preheated 200° oven for 8 hours.
Allow to cool in pan.
Unmold and chill before serving.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: easy alphabet soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients except mixed vegetables and pasta.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover & simmer 10-15 minutes or until celery and onion are crisp-tender.
Stir in mixed veggies and pasta, cover and cook over medium heat another 20-25 minutes until veggies and pasta are tender, stirring occasionally.
For heartier soup, add 1 lb. cooked ground beef or 2 c. cooked shredded chicken when mixed vegetables and pasta are added.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Dice the potatoes and onions.
Cook potatoes, onions, beef, tomatoes and spices until potatoes are done.
Add mixed vegetables, peas and corn.
Let simmer for 1 hour.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix flour, cake mix and eggs.
Add oil, water, strawberry jello and frozen strawberries.
Pour in two greased and floured cake pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost with icing.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix all of dressing ingredients except parmesan cheese well. Add cheese and mix again. Coat lettuce and croutons with dressing and add about 1/2 cup shredded parmesan cheese. For Croutons: cube about a half loaf of any kind of bread.
Heat olive oil, black pepper, garlic salt and fresh garlic.
Toss the bread cubes and turn constantly to coat and cook.
Be careful not to burn them. The croutons will need to sit out for awhile to become crisp.

title: creamy celery-seed dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vinegar, in small bowl.
Blend in vinegar.
Makes about 1/2 cup.

title: egg nog with cooked eggs
directions: Make a custard by cooking eggs, sugar, salt and 1 quart milk over low heat for 25 minutes or until back of spoon is coated.
Do not boil.
Pour custard in bowl and add second quart of milk.
Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Refrigerate until chilled, about 9 hours. Add brandy.

title: ham glaze
directions: Cook ingredients until preserves melt.
Spoon some glaze on ham while cooking.
Baste occasionally.
During last half hour of cooking, place apricot halves and more glaze on ham.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet and bake until golden brown. cool
Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Spread on cool crust.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Blend the ingredients.
Drizzle in 1 1/2 cups Bertolli olive oil.
Fold in 1/2 cup Parmesan or Romano cheese.

title: praline mousse
directions: Place the 1 1/2 cups of Praline Powder in a medium mixing bowl and set aside.
Beat egg whites, adding sugar slowly until peaks hold.
Fold egg whites into the Praline Powder.
Don't wash the bowl, just pour in the cream and whisk.
Add the vanilla and beat until soft peaks hold.
Fold the cream into the praline mixture. Pour into a 1-quart freezerproof bowl.
Sprinkle with the 1 tablespoon of Praline Powder.
Freeze at least 4 hours before serving.

title: "mama" old-fashioned banana pudding
directions: Beat egg whites stiff and add 8 tablespoons sugar for meringue. Bring milk to a boil.
Mix other ingredients, except wafers and bananas, and 1/4 cup milk together.
Add to boiling milk and, after it thickens, pour over layer of vanilla wafers and sliced bananas. Top with meringue and cook at 350° until meringue browns, about 10 minutes.

title: pickled celery sticks
directions: Clean celery and cut into strips.
Cut to fit in pint jars. Cut carrots the same.
In saucepan, cook carrots (covered) and boil for 2 minutes.
Add celery and cook for another 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain.
Put in hot pint
jars.
Combine water, vinegar, salt and spices.
Bring to boil.
Pour in jars.
Put on lids. Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients in large bowl.
Combine sugar, apple cider vinegar, eagle brand milk and mayo or miracle whip.
Pour over pasta mixture and refrigerate.
Makes 30 1/2 cup servings.

title: smothered field peas
directions: Saute onions in oil until golden brown, stirring frequently. Add 1/2 cup water, then simmer 8 minutes. Stir in peas and smother for 20 minutes. Add 1 cup water and smother for 15 minutes. Add the 5 cups water and cook for 45 minutes. Season to taste.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, softened butter and egg together with fork. Spread in bottom of cake pan and around sides, too.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese, 2 eggs and vanilla.
Pour this mixture over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: a warm home
directions: Take a cup of kindness.
Mix it well with love.
Add patience and faith.
Top with joy and cheer.
Sprinkle generously with happiness and you'll have a warm cozy home throughout the year. Serves all.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix together the buttermilk and egg in bowl.
Slice green tomatoes.
Dip into flour mixture, then in buttermilk and egg mixture.
Dip back into flour mixture and fry in hot vegetable oil until brown on both sides.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli in a 12 x 7 x 1-inch dish.
(Cook broccoli until tender-crisp first.)
Layer on chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter and bread crumbs and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: rocky road clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Beat until cool.
Stir in nuts, marshmallows and peanut butter.
Spoon clusters onto wax paper. Let cool.
When firm, eat!!!

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package. Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes. Cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread cheese and crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Beat egg; add all other
ingredients.
Drop by spoon and fry brown in cooking oil.

title: grandma's stuffed pork fillets
directions: Pound pork chops into thin cutlets.
Fill with a piece of cheese and a piece of ham, trimmed to fit inside of the cutlet. Salt and pepper them and add a dash of nutmeg.
Turn the edges of meat in and roll.
Hold together with toothpicks.
Coat with flour, egg and bread crumbs.
Place in hot oil, turning from time to time until brown.
Cooking time is approximately 15 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli.
Add all other ingredients and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in greased loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: easy meatloaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Grease 2 loaf pans and set aside. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well. Put mixture into loaf pans and bake for 30 minutes or until well done. Remove from oven, drain grease and serve. Slices well for sandwiches when cold.

title: date chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine dates, boiling water and 1 teaspoon soda.
Cream shortening and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour and remaining soda.
Mix with date mixture and shortening mixture. Turn into 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (8 x 8-inch) pans.
Top with 1/2 cup sugar, chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread over cake and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
This is a good cake; you don't need any frosting.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to soft ball.
Add peanuts.
Cook to hard crack (300° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and salt along with soda.
Stir really fast and place on buttered cookie sheet.

title: chow mein
directions: Cut meat into 1/2 to 3/4 inch pieces and brown in large skillet.
Sprinkle with salt, add onion and water.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for 45 minutes.
Add Cabbage and cook 10 minutes. Stir in bean sprouts and chop suey vegetables.
Blend soy sauce with cornstarch and ginger.
Gradually add to mixture, stirring to blend.
Cook until thicken, stirring occasionally.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Keep dough frozen.
Grease rectangular pan with butter.
If desired, sprinkle cinnamon, raisins and/or nuts in bottom of pan. Shake frozen dough balls in a bag with some cinnamon.
Lay balls side by side in rows in the pan.
Sprinkle the brown sugar over the dough balls.
Take the vanilla pudding (dry) and sprinkle over the brown sugar, then take the melted butter and pour on top of pudding mix.
Cover and let rise at room temperature overnight or at least 8 hours.
When dough has puffed up or is running over, bake in oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When done, turn over onto a cookie sheet.
Serves 18.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix pineapple juice, soy sauce, sherry or stock, garlic, parsley and pepper. Marinate chicken breasts for 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
(The marinade adds no significant calories.)
Grill chicken.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Add butter.
When melted, remove from heat and beat until it begins to thicken.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop a teaspoon at a time on greased waxed paper.

title: monkey bread
directions: In a large bowl, pour boiling water over Crisco and dissolve. Set aside to cool to lukewarm. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well; refrigerate overnight.

title: onion pie(this is joe's favorite)
directions: Make a crust of the crushed saltines and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Saute the onions in 1/4 cup butter or oleo until golden brown.
Put these on top of the cracker crumbs in a shallow casserole.
Sprinkle the grated cheese on top.
(This can be prepared ahead of time.)

title: pumpkin nut cookies
directions: Mix butter, eggs, sugar and pumpkin all together; set aside. Mix all dry ingredients: flour, baking powder, spices and walnuts. Mix the two mixtures together.
Preheat oven to 350° for about 15 minutes apiece.

title: standard pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add cold water, one tablespoon at a time, until easy to handle.
Divide dough in half.
Roll 1/8 inch thick on floured board, being careful not to add too much flour (that makes dough tough). Standard crust has 222 g fat in two crusts.

title: corn dogs
directions: Dip each hot dog in mixture; fry in deep fat.
Will cover approximately 20 hot dogs.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Cool and stir margarine, onion, salt and pepper over medium heat until onion is slightly tender.
Stir in flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir one minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Place macaroni in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir cheese sauce into macaroni. Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued short ribs
directions: Brown ribs in oil.
Simmer, covered in heavy pan on top of stove or in 300° preheated oven 1 hour.
Combine chili sauce, ketchup, celery seed, brown sugar, mustard, Worcestershire, vinegar and butter.
Remove ribs from pan; drain all liquids from pan.
Put ribs in pan; pour sauce over ribs.
Simmer, covered, for 3 hours or bake at 250° to 300°.
Stir occasionally so ribs won't stick and burn.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients to soft ball stage.
Stir in pecans, coating well.
Pour out onto wax paper.
Stir to separate.

title: marie's spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop celery, pepper, onion and garlic.
Saute in 3 tablespoons olive oil until tender.
Add hamburger; saute until browned.
Add tomatoes, sauce and paste.
Cook over low heat for 2 hours.
Serve over your favorite pasta.

title: stuffed breast of veal
directions: Have the butcher cut a deep pocket in the veal.
Saute one onion in the oil or shortening and add the chopped meat.
Add bread crumbs, half a can of tomato sauce, egg and salt and pepper.
Stuff the mixture into the veal pocket.
Sew end closed.
Slice the remaining onion and the celery with leaves into a roasting pan. Add the water.
Place veal in the pan, bone side down, and spread with the rest of the tomato sauce.
Bake 2 hours, covered.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes to brown.
Place veal on a large platter.
Strain gravy and thicken if desired with cornstarch diluted in a little cold water.
Bring to a boil.
Serve with the veal.

title: baked zucchini gratin
directions: In lightly greased 2 qt. baking dish (oblong), layer onions and zucchini slices.
Drizzle 1/4 cup melted oleo spread.
Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese.
Combine remaining oleo, bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle crumb mixture evenly over tops.
Bake at 350° for 35 - 40 minutes or until zucchini is fork tender.

title: dutch apple tart
directions: Pastry:
Combine flour, butter, 1/2 cup sugar and grated lemon rind.
Roll dough out to fit a 9-inch round cake pan with some dough left over to trim top.

title: chris' famous baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bacon.
Place in baking dish.
Lay bacon strips on top and bake in a 300° oven for about 2 hours or until bacon is done.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well each time.
Sift flour with powdered milk, baking powder and salt.
In a separate bowl, combine pineapple juice, lemon juice and vanilla extract.
Add flour mixture alternately with juice mixture to creamed butter and sugar, beating well with each addition.
Add coconut, stirring well.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Turn oven down to 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line pie tin with bottom pastry.
Melt butter in saucepan. Blend in flour, salt, pepper and thyme.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and top with pastry.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Mix the condensed milk and Cool Whip together.
Add the thawed lemonade.
Mixture will thicken at once.
Pour into a 9-inch graham cracker crust and refrigerate until serving.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix melted margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Brown together the ground beef and chopped onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer together for about 10 minutes. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese cake
directions: Put into blender the sour cream, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Blend for 1 minute.
Add cream cheese.
Blend until smooth. While still blending, add melted butter.
Pour into spring-form pan.
Bake in lower 1/3 of oven at 325° for 45 minutes.
It will look like it is not done, but is.
Turn on broiler until top browns.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
When you serve, spoon orange curd sauce over each slice.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Chill.

title: five pound tub fudge
directions: Place sugar, butter and milk in large pan, bring to boil, turn to simmer for 10 minutes or until a soft ball.
Pour over chips, marshmallows and nuts.
Stir and pour into buttered pan. (It is almost impossible to get this fudge too hard.)

title: noodles
directions: Mix and sift flour and salt.
Add gradually to egg until a stiff dough is formed.
Knead a few minutes on floured board. Roll out to 1/16-inch thickness.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Cut in long 1/4-inch wide strips.
Dry thoroughly.
Noodles may be cut into any size strips or any tiny fancy shapes.
This makes 1 1/2 cups raw noodles.

title: cole slaw
directions: Sprinkle cabbage with salt and let drain in a colander about 2 hours, squeezing as much water out as possible before continuing. May drain overnight, if desired.
Add onions.
In a small bowl, mix remaining ingredients and stir into cabbage.
Adjust seasonings if needed by adding a bit of sugar first and if necessary, more salt.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken veronique
directions: Squeeze lemon over chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add chicken; cook until browned and juices run clear, turning as needed.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
Reserve drippings in skillet.
Mix water and cornstarch in bowl; stir into drippings.
Add grapes and cream.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens.
Stir in wine.
Spoon sauce over chicken and serve.
Makes 2 servings.

title: my cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, flour and nuts.
Butter a 3-quart shallow baking dish and pour pineapple into it.
Top with flour mixture and pour butter over it.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain and chop shrimp.
Soften cream cheese and add all ingredients together.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.
Good with chips or party crackers.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Have ready 8 or 9-inch tin pie pans, sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.
Use a large, heavy pot.

title: grilled chicken jerk seasoning
directions: Coarsely puree first 10 ingredients in food processor.
Pour puree into large bowl.
Add chicken breasts and turn to coat. Cover and refrigerate 3 hours or overnight, turning occasionally. Remove from marinade and grill.
Baste with marinade; serve marinade on side.

title: maucia's orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and 3 cups flour, alternating with 1/2 cup buttermilk.
In another bowl, mix 1/2 cup flour with nuts, dates, orange slices and coconut; mix together. Add to cake batter.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours or longer, until done.
Glaze while cake is still hot.

title: apricot and lemon sherbet
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; cool.
Add sugar, apricot juice, apricots which have been put through a sieve and the cream (whipped).
Mix and freeze in refrigerator or in a crank or electric ice cream freezer.
If frozen in refrigerator, when mixture becomes mushy, remove and beat with electric mixer. Return to freezer.
Serve with fresh mint.
Serves 8.

title: coconut cake supreme
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions in two 9-inch round cake pans.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar and melted margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa.
Add pecans.
Pour into well-greased pan or unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and top with whipped topping.

title: skip's favorite chicken and black bean enchiladas
directions: Cut chicken into short, thin strips.
Cook bacon in 10-inch skillet until crisp.
Remove to paper towel; crumble.
Pour off all, but 2 tablespoons, drippings.
Cook and stir chicken and garlic in drippings until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir in 1/2 cup picante sauce, beans, red pepper, cumin and salt.
Simmer until thickened, 7 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in green onions and reserved bacon.

title: popover pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Brown beef with onion in large skillet, breaking it up with a spoon as it cooks.
Drain excess fat from skillet.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon into prepared pan; top with slices of cheese.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Melt oleo; add flour, stirring to make smooth paste.
Add milk and blend with wire whisk until well mixed.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve on toast points or English muffins.
Great for brunch.
Serves 15!

title: beef roulades
directions: Cut steak into 4 serving size pieces.
Using a meat mallet, pound each piece to 1/8-inch thick.
Spread one side of each beef piece with 1/4 of the mustard.
Place 2 green pepper strips or a green onion at a short end of each beef piece and roll up.
Secure with wooden toothpick.
Spray a large cold skillet with cooking spray.
Heat skillet over medium heat.
Add beef rollups; brown on all sides.
Remove rolls from skillet.
Add chopped onions to skillet and cook for 3 minutes or until onion is nearly tender.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together beef broth and flour.
Pour mixture into skillet.
Cook until thickened and bubbly.
Add chopped carrots and beef rolls.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: microwave coconut mochi
directions: Mix together mochiko, sugar, coconut milk, water, vanilla extract and red food coloring with an electric mixer until all lumps dissolve.
Lightly grease microwavable Bundt pan with Pam and pour mixture into pan.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Microwave on Medium-high heat for 15 minutes and 5 minutes on High (adjust accordingly with your microwave).
Cool for approximately 1 hour. Cut with plastic knife and roll in potato starch.
Store in airtight container (Tupperware).

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix in saucepan and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add and bring to a boil 1/2 bottle catsup, 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce and a few drops of hot sauce.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and chill. Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: turkey steaks with herb butter
directions: Cut turkey into four 1/2-inch slices. Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Heat turkey over hot coals in covered grill 8 to 10 minutes, turning once and brushing occasionally with butter mixture.
Makes 4 servings containing 235 calories per serving.

title: date nut bread
directions: In medium bowl, mix boiling water, orange juice and dates and let stand until at room temperature.
Heat oven to 325°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan with unsalted shortening and coat lightly with flour.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a big bowl.
Stir until the batter is well mixed.
Grease several cookie sheets with butter or margarine so the cookies won't stick when they are baking.
You can use paper towels or wax paper to spread the butter or margarine.
Drop the batter by the teaspoonful onto cookie sheets. Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes about 48 cookies.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco, eggs and sugar.
Beat 3 to 4 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until well blended and then beat 2 more minutes on high.
Pour in tube pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Brown ground beef well.
While browning, add onion, garlic, oregano, thyme, salt and pepper.
When beef is done, drain all juices off.
Add cheese and beaten eggs.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted.
Mixture will be very stiff and dry.
Cook manicotti according to package directions.
Using a teaspoon, stuff meat mixture into shells.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Pour half the salsa into the bottom of the pan, under shells. Pour remaining salsa over shells.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: indian cornbread
directions: Mix together the egg, milk, oil, cornbread mix, sugar and corn.
Pour half of the batter into a well-greased 8-inch round or square pan.
Spread green chiles on top of batter.
Put cheese over chiles and cover with the remaining batter.
Bake 25 minutes at 450°.
Serve hot with butter.

title: italian dream cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Separate eggs and add egg yolks to sugar mixture.
Also add buttermilk, soda, vanilla, margarine, pecans, flour and coconut.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into batter.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: salad or dessert
directions: Mix and freeze.
Take out of freezer 1/2 hour before using. Can be refrozen.

title: cheddar squash bake
directions: Scrub squash and trim off ends; do not peel.
Cook whole, covered, in boiling, salted water for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Cut into thin slices and sprinkle with salt (you have about 6 cups).
Reserve a few slices squash for garnish.
Mix together egg yolks, sour cream and flour.
Fold in egg whites.
Layer half the squash, egg mixture and cheese in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle bacon over.
Repeat layers. Combine crumbs and butter or margarine.
Sprinkle over the top. Arrange reserved squash on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Garnish with bacon curls and parsley sprig, if desired. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cranberry and sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
While still hot, add gelatine that has been dissolved in 1/4 cup cold water.
Chill until syrupy, then add cranberry sauce.
Chill again until syrupy, then add sour cream and nuts.
Pour into mold and chill 4 hours before serving or overnight.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange broccoli in casserole.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and water.
Let cool and pour over vegetables.

title: kitty's meat loaf
directions: Saute onions in shortening in a large skillet. Add hamburger and 1 tablespoon flour.
Brown.
Stir in milk, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper. Simmer until thick, about 15 minutes. Stir in parsley; set aside.

title: ribbon cookies
directions: Cream the oleo, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add the flour, salt and baking powder.
Divide dough in half and add to 1 section 1 square melted, unsweetened chocolate and 1/4 cup chopped nuts. Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with waxed paper.
Pack dough in layers.
Cover with waxed paper and chill at least overnight.
Cut in thirds lengthwise, then slice 1/4 inch thick.
Bake 1 inch apart at 350° for 10 minutes on ungreased pan.
Do not brown!

title: rocky road nut cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts and 1 cup oleo. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Combine brown sugar, 1/2 cup oleo, milk and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix until smooth. Drizzle over marshmallows.

title: "sloppy joes" casserole(children's favorite)
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off grease.
Cook macaroni as package directs.
To hamburger, add tomato sauce, paste, seasoning mix and 1 cup of water.
Layer 1/2 noodles and cottage cheese in bottom of a 2-quart dish.
Add 1/2 of meat mixture, then repeat. Heat approximately 10 minutes in microwave and top with cheese.

title: florida's famous blue ribbon pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour 3 small loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 325°. Beat eggs.
Mix in sugar, pumpkin and water.
Add oil.
Combine the next 4 ingredients well.
Stir into pumpkin mixture until blended. Add nuts.
Bake 1/2 hour at 325°, then at 300° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour longer.
Tester should come out clean.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Add and beat shortening, sugar, eggs, applesauce, vanilla and water with raisins.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with 1 cup chopped pecans. Refrigerate until firm.
Roll into ball and roll out remaining nuts until coated.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine oil, sugar, vinegar, salt, lemon juice and pepper. Mix well and pour over vegetables.
Chill over 4 hours or overnight.
Stir occasionally.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook and drain hamburger meat.
Add onions, salt, pepper, garlic salt and celery salt.
Add spaghetti sauce and cook for 15 minutes.
Add cottage cheese and eggs.
Pour sauce over layer of cooked noodles, top with shredded cheese.
Repeat until out of sauce with cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour at 400° in a covered dish.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each breast with bacon.
Cover bottom of flat, greased baking dish (8 x 12 x 2-inch) with chipped beef.
Mix soup, sour cream, sherry and milk.
Pour over all and refrigerate until ready to bake.
Bake at 275° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Can be made ahead.

title: rice pilaf with lamb and vegetables(to serve 6)
directions: Heat the oil in a heavy 10 to 12-inch skillet over high heat until a light haze forms above it.

Drop in the lamb cubes and fry them for 5 to 8 minutes, turning them constantly with a large spoon until they are lightly and evenly browned on all sides. With a slotted spoon transfer the cubes of lamb to a heavy 4-quart casserole.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes a very large casserole.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Shred washed lettuce with a knife.
Place in large bowl and set aside.
Fry bacon until crisp, then crumble.
Place bacon on top of lettuce.
Scramble 6 eggs in 2 tablespoons margarine; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour on top of lettuce and bacon, then toss for 1 to 2 minutes until thoroughly mixed.
Serve immediately. Great with sliced tomatoes and corn bread.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: A recipe for children to make.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup 4 minutes on High, mixing well.
Add peanuts and cook 4 more minutes on High.
Add butter and vanilla, blending well.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes on High.
Peanuts will be slightly browned, syrup very hot.
Add soda and stir gently until light and foamy.
Pour mixture into lightly greased cookie sheet. Cool about 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces.
Yields 1 pound.

title: mountain mama's mudslide cake
directions: Combine flour, oleo and nuts.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Mix together cream cheese and powdered sugar; fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on baked mixture.

title: sausage chili
directions: Brown onion and sausage.
Mix the rest of ingredients together and simmer 20 minutes.

title: beef and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Cut beef across grain into thin slices.
Combine 1 tablespoon each of cornstarch and soy sauce with sugar, ginger and garlic; stir in beef.
Stand 15 minutes.
Remove broccoli flowerets; cut stalks crosswise into 1/8-inch slices.
Combine remaining cornstarch and soy sauce with 1 cup of water; set aside.
Heat 1 teaspoon of oil in wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add meat; stir-fry 1 minute.
Remove.
Heat rest of oil and add broccoli, onion and carrot; stir-fry 4 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Stir in meat and soy sauce mixture; bring to a boil.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens.

title: sugar-free carrot cake(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs; add Sugar Twin, water and oil.
Sift dry ingredients together and slowly add to egg mixture.
Add carrots, pecans and pineapple.
Spread in prepared pan and bake for 40 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: beef jerky
directions: Semi-freeze the steak.
Cut into thin strips with the grain. Marinate overnight in the mixture.
Drain and put strips on racks. Put racks in oven and dry at lowest temperature with the door ajar. This will take about 4 to 6 hours.
Cool and store in airtight container.
Great for camping.

title: turtle tots
directions: Boil turtle pieces until tender; dip into egg/milk mixture (blended well).
Roll in bread or cracker crumbs.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Serve with your favorite vegetable.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: sausage stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut tops from tomatoes; scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact. Chop pulp.
Combine pulp, bread crumbs, celery, green pepper and cooked sausage; mix well.
Sprinkle insides of shells with salt and pepper.
Arrange tomatoes in an 8-inch square baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until tomatoes are thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle tomatoes with cheese.
Bake for 1 minute, or until cheese melts.
Sprinkle parsley over top, if desired.

title: sugarless fruit salad
directions: Put in large bowl and add 20 pks. of equal or 1/3 cup fructose.
Take the 3 cups of fruit juice and put in large bowl. Mix large pack of jello instant pudding and pie filling.
Put in juice and beat until thick.
Pour over fruit and garnish with Kiwi fruit slices and maraschino cherries.
Add a few nuts.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Combine; sprinkle mixture over blueberries and cook at 350° until top is golden brown.

title: old fashioned banana cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix Pet milk with lemon juice.
Add alternately to dry ingredients with butter and bananas.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake 40 minutes or until cakes spring back when lightly touched with finger in 350° oven.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Put everything except vanilla into a pan and bring to a boil; cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla.
Store sauce in the refrigerator.
When reheating do not bring to a boil. Serve warm over ice cream, etc.

title: harvest pound cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs.
Add baby food.
Mix dry ingredients. Put both mixtures together and mix well.
Add nuts and bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour at 351°.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Refrigerate while veggies are marinating. The flavor improves the longer the vegetables are kept. The dish can be added to without losing its flavor.

title: dirt cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Oreos.
Mix well.
Line bottom of clean plant pot with Cool Whip lid on wax paper.
Starting with cookie crumbs, layer mixtures. Chill overnight.
Decorate with artificial flower with stem wrapped in foil.
Serve with clean hand shovel.
Watch the expressions.

title: oven stew
directions: In a large Dutch oven or roaster, combine tomatoes with liquid, tapioca, basil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add cubed beef, onions, carrots, potatoes, celery and water.
Mix well.
Cover. Bake in 350° oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours (or at 300° for 3 hours). May stir when half done.
It makes its own gravy and freezes well. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix well. Spoon into muffin pan, lined with muffin cups. Freeze until firm, then store in plastic bags in freezer.

title: beet relish
directions: Heat all together until boiling.
Divide into plastic containers and freeze or place in refrigerator and allow to marinate 1 day.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Boil 10 minutes and pour over vegetables.
You may use whatever fresh vegetables you desire.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Reserve one cup of strawberries, then mash one cup.
Mix with cornstarch and sugar.
Bring to a boil and cool.
Then add remaining fresh berries.

title: cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add mandarin juice and mandarin peel, then blend in flour mixture.
Chill dough a few minutes until it can be rolled easily.

Roll out on floured board to 1/8-inch thick or thinner. Cut with fancy cutters and place on lightly greased baking sheets. Bake in moderate oven, 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes, depending on thickness of cookies.
Remove to wire racks and brush while warm with glaze.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: gravy(a breakfast staple)
directions: Heat bacon drippings. Add flour and stir until flour is lightly browned, about 3 minutes, over medium heat. Add mixture of evaporated milk and water, stirring constantly.
After mixture begins to boil, cook for another minute.
Serve with biscuits and sausage.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour, cream of tartar and soda.
Combine jam and sour cream, adding to creamed mixture alternating with flour mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans; bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool 10 minutes then remove from pans.
Cool completely on wire racks.

title: fiesta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add Fritos and dressing when ready to serve.

title: pastry shell
directions: Combine flour and salt. Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle cold water (one tablespoon at a time) evenly over surface. Stir with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened. Shape into a ball.
Chill 5 minutes. Roll pastry to about 1/4-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Place in a 9-inch pie plate.
Trim off excess pastry along edges. Fold edges under and crimp.
Prick sides and bottom of pastry with a fork. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: picante sauce
directions: Process tomatoes in food processor and drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Put in scalded pint jars and seal.
Water bath for 15 minutes.

title: nutmeg almond float
directions: Add sugar, nutmeg, salt and flavorings to milk and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into chilled glasses and top with ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses and optional ingredients well and form into a ball.
Top with walnuts.
Serve with Ritz or Town House crackers.

title: cornbread
directions: Grease pan with oil (heat in oven).
Mix all ingredients. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: chili beans
directions: Chop onions and pepper.
Brown in oil.
Add meat and brown. Add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together oil, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 55 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels in the microwave or double boiler.
Remove from heat and stir in noodles and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet or waxed paper.
Let stand until formed.

title: best whole wheat bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add shortening, sugar and salt and stir until dissolved.
Add whole wheat flour and beat rapidly with spoon. Add dissolved yeast and cold water.
Mix well, then add enough white flour to make a nice soft dough.
Let rise until double, then punch down and rise again.
Shape into 3 loaves.
Let rise and bake.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in a 9 x 13-inch dish and melt in oven.
In mixing bowl, stir sugar, flour, baking soda, salt and milk until well blended.
Pour batter over melted butter. Do not stir!
Place peaches evenly over batter.
Sprinkle sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mushroom wild rice
directions: Wash wild rice in 3 changes of hot water.
Drain.
Combine rice, 2 cups water and bouillon granules in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce to low and simmer 30 to 45 minutes or until rice is tender and water is absorbed.
Saute mushrooms in butter and lemon juice until tender.
Stir mushrooms, onion, parsley, garlic powder and nuts into rice.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add confectioners sugar until of spreading consistency.

title: white chocolate macadamia nut cookie mix
directions: Layer ingredients into jar in order given.
Press each layer firmly before adding the next ingredient.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and oleo in large bowl. Add yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and sour cream alternately; blend in well.
Add flavoring.
Beat egg whites, pinch of salt and 4 level teaspoons sugar until stiff; fold into mixture.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: al's pecan pie
directions: Mix Karo, sugar, salt, eggs, vanilla, pecans and melted butter.
Add to unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 225° for 60 minutes until done.

title: super saltine heath bars
directions: Line a cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Cover foil with whole saltine crackers.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter and add brown sugar.
Bring to a boil; continue to boil for 2 minutes. Then pour over crackers.
Bake for 4 minutes.
Cover with chocolate chips, then spread melted chips to make an icing. Refrigerate.
Break into pieces.

title: baked artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly. Service with Melba toast rounds.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix
the refried beans and taco seasoning mix; place on serving
platter.
Mix
the
avocado
dip and sour cream; pour onto
the
bean mixture.
Top this layer with cheese, tomatoes and green onions. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Cut beef with scissors and blend with olives.
Mix with the rest.
Soften cheese and mayonnaise.
Soak the onion in sherry for 5 minutes.
Add onion mix and olives last.
Serve with crackers.

title: date roll
directions: Mix well. Shape into a roll, then roll in wax paper and refrigerate.
Slice and serve with whipped topping.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt together; cut in butter or shortening.
Add raisins and caraway seed.
Mix well.
Add egg and buttermilk and mix to smooth dough. Knead on floured board about one minute.
Shape into a ball, cut a cross and sprinkle with a teaspoon of sugar.
Bake in greased cake pan or cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°, then for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon cake filling
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt thoroughly; add lemon juice and rind, then water, eggs and butter. Blend well and cook in double boiler until smooth. Stir constantly while boiling. Spread on white cake layers (5 or 6 thin layers).

title: apple muffins
directions: Beat together egg, milk and oil.
Add dry ingredients and mix gently.
Stir in apples.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full and bake for 20 to 30 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until thickened.
Add peanut butter and mix.
Pour in ice cream can.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 1/2 hour.
Add cream, vanilla and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into can.
Add milk to fill line.
Stir well.
Place in ice cream maker and churn. When ice cream is getting soft, put broken chunks of candy in all at once and continue to let ice cream churn.

title: oven-fried chicken with herb biscuits
directions: Heat oven to
Heat margarine in rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch,
in oven until melted.
Mix baking mix, salt, paprika and pepper;
coat
chicken.
Place	chicken, skin side down, in pan.
Bake	35 minutes.
Prepare Herb Biscuits.
Turn chicken, pushing to one
side of pan.
Drop dough by spoonfuls into pan in single layer next to chicken.
Bake until biscuits are light brown and
chicken is done, about 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: refrigerator spoon rolls(no rising time required)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add all other ingredients and beat until well mixed.
Place in airtight container and refrigerate until needed.
As needed, spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
The dough can be kept a week.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites, vanilla and salt together with wire whisk or in mixer, adding sugar gradually until stiff.
Add butterscotch chips.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Place in preheated oven.
Turn off oven.
Take out in the A.M.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine macaroni, cheese, sweet milk, mayonnaise and cream of mushroom soup. Pour into baking dish. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until bubbly around edges.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Cut chicken bite size.
Mix chicken and all ingredients together.
Cover.
Let marinate in refrigerator overnight, stirring 3 times.
Cook in microwave 10 to 12 minutes on High.
Time depends on wattage.
Serve with rice or noodles and fresh whole string beans.

title: rachel's dip
directions: Spread cream cheese evenly on bottom of oven-safe deep, round or sheet pan.
Cover with one can chili, layer of mushrooms and another can of chili.
Add jalapeno juice and 6 to 8 slices of jalapeno, if desired.
Place a layer of Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake or heat until hot or bubbles, approximately 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Doritos or tortilla chips.

title: eggplant
directions: Slice eggplant.
Combine flour, onion powder, salt and pepper. Coat eggplant in flour mixture well.
Fry on medium-high heat until brown on both sides.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: hot dip
directions: Melt in double boiler. Serve with bread sticks, chips or crackers.

title: mediterranean chicken pockets
directions: Brush a nonstick skillet with olive oil and heat over medium-high flame. Add chicken breasts and saut, turning frequently, until cooked and no longer pink, about 8 to 10 minutes. Cover and let cool in the refrigerator.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix cheese and Ro-Tel in crock-pot.
Brown hamburger and sausage in skillet with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Add to cheese mixture.
Dip with favorite chips and enjoy.

title: rave review cake
directions: Mix cake and pudding mix, water, oil, and eggs in large bowl. Beat a medium speed.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Pour in greased and floured 10 inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Cool.

title: cinnamon apple salad
directions: Dissolve 1/2 cup cinnamon drops in 1 cup boiling water.
When dissolved, add cold water to make 2 cups.
Add to jello.
When jello starts to set, add applesauce and chill.

title: cherry streusel
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar, eggs, one at a time, vanilla and butter.
Mix well.
Add sour cream and blend well once more.
Spread half of batter into well-greased 12-inch tube pan.
Spread cherry filling over layer of batter.
Pour remaining batter evenly over cherries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: caramel sweet potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Put sliced sweet potatoes in skillet.
Sprinkle with salt, sugar and flour.
Cook and simmer until sugar is thickened.

title: devilish eggs
directions: Cut thin slice off ends of eggs. Halve eggs crosswise. Remove yolks to bowl; mash. Stir in remaining ingredients. Spoon mixture into whites. Place eggs on platter; cover loosely. Refrigerate at least 2 hours or up to a day. Top with additional chives, if desired. Makes 12 servings.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute garlic, onion and green pepper in bacon grease.
Add olives, beans, bacon and tomato sauce.
Simmer until thickened and heated thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: syrup ginger cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and syrup together.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
May add some raisins and nuts.
Bake in a moderate oven (325° to 350°) until done.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Add first 5 ingredients and cover with water.
Cook approximately 1/2 hour.
Add eggs and tomato soup; cook about 5 or 10 minutes more.

title: ten minute beef stir-fry
directions: Cut beef crosswise (against the grain) into very thin slices and sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium high heat, heat 2 teaspoons oil and add beef. Cook and stir for 2 to 3 minutes until browned.
Using slotted spoon, remove beef to plate.
In same skillet over medium high heat, heat remaining teaspoon of oil and add garlic.
Cook and stir for 30 to 60 seconds until fragrant.
Add frozen vegetables, 1/4 cup water and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Cook covered for 3 minutes until tender.
Meanwhile, in small bowl, stir peanut and remaining 1/2 cup water to blend.
Add to skillet along with beef and any accumulated juices.
Cook stirring for 1 to 2 minutes longer until heated through and coated with sauce. Makes 4 servings.

title: ham and swiss buns
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Flour your working surface and separate rolls into 4 rectangles each; pinch holes closed.
Flour rolling pin; roll each to 7 x 5-inch area.
Arrange ham and cheese to fit, leaving 1/2 inch of dough all around.
Spread filling with mustard. Brush edge of dough with some egg; fold dough and filling over, so that 5 sides meet.
Press edges with fork to seal.
Place on cookie sheet; brush with egg.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, until brown.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Grease and flour half of the sheet pans.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Turn cake out on waxed sheet that has been dusted with powdered sugar.
Roll up long side. Cool for 30 minutes.
Unroll and spread with filling.
Roll back up and chill for 1 hour before slicing.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Prepare carrots for cooking.
Slice and cook in salted water until tender; drain.
Arrange carrots, onions and peppers in layers.
Make a marinade by combining remaining ingredients.
Pour marinade over carrots.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving. The marinated carrots will keep in the refrigerator for over a week.

title: tea cake cookies
directions: Mix,
sugar,
shortening,
eggs, soda, baking powder and water.
Make
a
nest in flour.
Put mixture in nest, work with hands until
you
work
enough flour in to roll out.
Then cut. Bake on cookie sheet at 400° until brown, about 12 minutes.

title: fig nut cake
directions: Sift flour and mix all ingredients. Blend well and pour in greased tube pan. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients for 4 minutes.
Add flour and soda. Drop on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: best ever pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour to mixture, alternating with milk.
Mix well.
Don't overbeat.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, place vanilla wafers on bottom of pan and then slice bananas on top of vanilla wafers.
Keep alternating vanilla wafers and bananas until the pan is full.

title: ann's easy biscuits
directions: Mix, roll and cut. Bake at 400° until brown (about 15 to 20 minutes).

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, salt and butter thoroughly.
Beat egg, lemon rind and extract into creamed mixture until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Gradually stir into creamed ingredients.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on floured board.
Cut into shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes or until light brown. Remove to cooling rack.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: baked kibbee(kibbee bi saineeya)
directions: Soak burghul in enough water to cover.
Grind pepper, onion, mint and basil and add to meat.
Add salt, spices and burghul. Squeezed to remove all water from burghul before adding to meat. Mix meat mixture by hand till well blended.
Add ice water as you mix to keep meat soft.
Generously oil a 9x13 baking dish.
Take meat mixture and place in dish, patting down evenly.
Cut into diamond shapes.
Pour additional oil on top of meat.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 30-40 mins. or until browned.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix thoroughly beef, 1/2 can tomato soup, onion soup mix, cracker crumbs, egg and 1/4 cup milk if mixture is too dry.
Firmly shape meat in 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Spread remaining soup evenly over
meat loaf.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until done.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle on top and bake about 15 or 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix ingredients as stated, then chill before serving.
Serves 10 to 15 people.

title: 8 minute cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth. Gradually add sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust.
Chill at least 4 hours. Top with strawberries or cherry/blueberry pie filling.

title: party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Makes 5 gallons.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Combine water, oil and sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Add eggs.
Add all dry ingredients to this and the grated potatoes.
Blend well.
Pour into a loaf pan that has been well greased.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ma elsie gue's applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add applesauce and raisins.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° in 2 greased loaf pans, placeed on rack close to bottom of oven.
Turn onto wire rack to cool after 2 minutes out of the oven.
Store in closed container with a piece of apple to keep moist.

title: mrs. fields' chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and brown sugar. Add eggs and mix together. Add remaining ingredients and mix together. Drop cookie dough onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: sliced meat roll-ups
directions: Remove stack of meat and cut stack in half diagonally.
Wrap half slices around pickle spear, celery, carrots or other crisp vegetables.
Secure with pick.
Makes 20 roll-ups.
Contains 20 calories each.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Drain peaches. Spread soft butter in bottom of a deep square 9 x 9-inch pan. Pack brown sugar evenly over butter.
Arrange peaches upside-down on sugar.
(Can use maraschino cherries between peaches, if desired.)

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off fat and set aside. In a saucepan, add together soup, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce, sliced olives, water and cornstarch.
Over medium heat, cook until slightly thick.
Remove from heat and add ground beef to sauce mix.
In a baking dish, make layers with cheeses, sauce and tortillas.
Finish off with meat and cheeses.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts in halves or quarters as desired.
Fold 2 to 3 slices chipped beef under chicken and wrap Sizzlean around both.
Place in baking dish.
Mix together golden mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours. This can be put together as far ahead as the day before cooked.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Cook to a firm ball.
Remove from heat.
Add the powdered sugar, butter and food coloring.
Mix well and drop by spoon on wax paper; let cool.

title: chocolate streusel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine the first 3 ingredients.
Cut in margarine until crumbly (mixture should be dry).
Reserve 2 cups of crumbs.
Press remainder on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Add eggs, one at a time, and beat all ingredients until well mixed (about 3 minutes).
Bake in Bundt pan sprayed with Pam at 315° for 45 minutes or until done.
When baked, add glaze.

title: mint layer cake
directions: Bake 30 minutes at 350 F. (or do what I do and use a brownie mix for the cake).

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; cream together.
If you want pineapple in your bread, add it in now. Add flour and all the other dry ingredients; blend well.
Mix in nuts with a spoon.
Turn mixture into 2 greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let cool in pan.

title: fresh apple coffee cake
directions: Combine apples, 1/4 cup orange juice and cinnamon in medium bowl; stir well.
Set aside.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup orange juice and milk; stir well.
Set aside.
Cream margarine. Gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add egg substitute and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir well.
Gradually add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with milk mixture.
Pour 1/2 of butter into a 10-inch tube pan coated with cooking spray; top with 1/2 of apple mixture.
Pour remaining batter into pan. Top with remaining apple mixture.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar
and oleo; add eggs and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Flatten with damp cloth over bottom of glass and
sprinkle
with
sugar.
Bake
at
350° for about 12 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook first five ingredients until tender in a small amount of water.
Add can of tomatoes (undrained).
Place in casserole dish. Cover with grated cheese.
Top with melted margarine and bread crumb mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes, until bread crumbs are brown and cheese is melted.

title: cocoa spice cake
directions: Sift flour, then measure and sift again with baking powder, salt, cocoa, cinnamon and cloves. Cream shortening and add sugar; beat well and add eggs, one at a time. Beat real well. Add cold potatoes; beat until smooth. Add milk and vanilla; beat again. Add all dry ingredients, raisins and nuts. Bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: dutch country grill
directions: To make sandwiches, in bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, apple, sugar and cinnamon.
Add chicken.
Spread each of 6 slices bread each with about 1/3 cup of chicken mixture.
Top with remaining slices of bread.
In skillet, melt butter.

title: italian chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Mix baking powder, cocoa, flour and seasonings and add to creamed mixture.
Beat in eggs, juice, whiskey and milk.
Fold in nuts and raisins and then drop batter by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and molasses.
Then add dry ingredients.
Add hot water last.
Beat until smooth.
Batter is thin, but makes a nice cake.
Bake in greased 12 x 9-inch cake pan at 350° for 35 minutes or little longer. This cake is very good with brown sugar icing.

title: eclairs by evelyn
directions: Heat water and butter until boiling; stir in flour.
Stir vigorously on low heat for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; beat in eggs one at a time until smooth.
Roll in shape of fingers.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Split and fill with pudding. Top with chocolate icing.

title: praline cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla. Add flour and pecans. Mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and salad oil.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg and add to first mixture along with vanilla.
Add apples and nuts (optional).
Before baking, mix brown sugar, melted oleo or butter, coconut and 1/2 cup nuts and put on top.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 1 hour. No frosting is needed.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding with mixer.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip. Alternate layers of wafers, bananas and pudding mixture in large bowl. Refrigerate.

title: carol's cornbread
directions: Combine all in bowl.
Stir until moistened.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (or 14 muffin tin).
Bake at 400° for 17 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in an unbaked pie crust. Start at 400° for 15 minutes, then turn to 300° for 30 minutes or more.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon in bowl. Mix until crumbly.
Press 1/2 in greased 9-inch layer pan.
Cover with rhubarb.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla in saucepan.
Cook, stirring until thick and clear.
Pour over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: grandma's cookies
directions: Mix butter and the powdered sugar until smooth.
Add vanilla. Blend together flour, salt and baking powder.
(Note:
Just a dash.)
Add flour mixture to butter mixture; blend well.
Add chopped nuts; blend.
Roll dough into two balls.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill 1 hour.
Flatten dough out.
Cut into 15 to 16 pieces.
Shape into marble balls.
Place on ungreased pan.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
While hot, roll into powdered sugar or dust.
Let cool.
Roll again.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: bavarian apple torte
directions: Cream butter, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Blend in flour.
Spread dough on bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan. Mix cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar.
Add egg and vanilla and mix. Pour into pan over dough.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Toss in apples. Spoon apple mixture over cream cheese.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: chocolate strawberry shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 8-inch round baking pan.
Combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut butter or margarine into dry ingredients until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add chocolate pieces.
Stir in milk just until moistened.
Spread dough into prepared pan, building up edges slightly.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes. Cool on wire rack 10 minutes.
Spoon half the strawberries and half the whipped cream over bottom layer and top with second layer. Spoon remaining strawberries and whipped cream over top.
Serve with hot fudge sauce.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, salt, milk, sugar and flour.
Mix well in microwavable bowl.
Microwave on Full power for 2 minutes.
Stir; return and microwave another 2 minutes.
Stir and return to microwave for an additional 2 minutes.

title: dad's pizzelles
directions: Beat ingredients together beginning with eggs and then follow as listed; mix well.
Preheat pizzelle iron.
Put a teaspoon of mix on center of each design.
Close lid.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Remove with fork; cool.

title: quick chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in a large pot.
Cover with water.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from bones.
Save broth.
Combine flour and baking powder. Cut in shortening.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Turn out on floured surface and knead lightly 4 to 5 times.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into strips.
Drop dumplings into pot.
Cover. Simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems. Broil rounded side up for 5 minutes. Combine crab meat, cream and Tabasco sauce. Turn mushrooms and fill with crab meat mixture.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over tops and broil again 5 to 10 minutes until tops are lightly browned.

title: potato sausage casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in slices.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish (spray dish with Pam).
Cut up cabbage and place on top (you may use more or less cabbage, whatever you like).
Season with parsley, basil, salt and pepper.
Brown the sausage links and place in casserole.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water and pour over casserole.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°, until potatoes are soft.
Mix up and serve.

title: hot taco spread
directions: Spread cream cheese in an 8 ounce pie pan; cover with chili. Add diced chilies and top with cheese.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix together oil, eggs and cake mix.
Slowly add milk, then pudding.
Pour batter into 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: nana morse's shredded wheat bread
directions: Pour boiling water over shredded wheat biscuits.
Add salt, sugar, molasses and shortening.
Let stand until cool.
Dissolve yeast in 2/3 cup warm water.
Add to mixture; add flour until dough is of workable consistency.
Knead well on floured board. Place ball of dough in greased bowl and allow to rise until double in size.
Punch down dough.
Divide into 2.
Place in greased pans and allow to rise until double in size.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Brush baked loaves with melted butter.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: burritos
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add refried beans and picante sauce.
Heat until well blended.
Warm tortillas in oven or microwave and keep warm. Fill with hamburger mixture and top with taco sauce, sour cream, lettuce, tomatoes and cheese as desired.

title: brandied cranberries
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold with poultry or pork.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: sondra's spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Stir in soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until blended.
Stir in spinach, water chestnuts and onions.
Cover and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: grilled lamb chops with rosemary
directions: Heat grill on high. Melt butter in small saucepan. Add rosemary. Grill chops on high. Baste with rosemary and butter. Turn and repeat. Serves 2.

title: jo an's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, saving 1/4 cup of tomato sauce.
Shape into loaf and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add remaining tomato sauce approximately 1/2 hour before end.*
Best if, after shaped into loaf, mixture is wrapped in cellophane wrap and stored in refrigerator overnight.
This allows flavors to blend.
Also, recommend baking in roasting pan, not loaf pan.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: light, tasty biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening with fork until mixture resembles coarse corn meal. Add milk and blend lightly with fork, until flour is moistened and dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead lightly for 30 seconds.
Roll 3/4-inch thick.
Place on lightly greased pan and brush tops of biscuits with butter or margarine.
Bake at 475° (very hot oven) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: steeplechase brunch
directions: Butter 1 side of the bread with softened butter and set aside. Melt 1/3 cup butter and brown mushrooms and onions over medium heat for 5 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Season to taste with salt and pepper; drain and set aside.

title: fudge pies
directions: Mix well and pour into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Nuts are optional.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake, uncovered, in a casserole dish for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer covered for 10 minutes.
Serve with hamburgers, chops, broilers, etc.
Very tasty over leftover roast, sliced.

title: maids of honor
directions: Put eggs in bowl, beat in sugar, lemon peel, juice, almonds, cream and nutmeg.
Beat until mix is smooth.
Put pastry in tart pans and fill half-way with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until filling has turned golden and almost set.

title: olives
directions: Soak olives overnight in fresh water. Drain.
Mix
2 ounces lye per 1 gallon water. Soak olives in this solution. Drain everyday for 3 days. Change water twice a day for 5 days. Dissolve 4 ounces rock salt per gallon.
Let stand 3 days. Drain. Dissolve 6 ounces salt per gallon.
Let stand 4 days.
Dissolve 6 ounces salt in water and leave. "Delicious."

title: shepherd's pie(health conscious)
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Mash together with skim milk and pepper until smooth; keep warm.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute ground beef.
Pour into colander lined with paper towels and drain fat.
Return meat to pan.
Add onion; cook until onion is translucent.
Add bell pepper, carrots, peas, tomato, parsley, chicken stock, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in water; stir into meat mixture.
Spoon into baking dish.
Spread mashed potatoes over surface.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Crumble sausage and fry until brown.
Mix with other ingredients; pour into casserole dish.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Add to cheese accent and Worcestershire sauce and mix well.
Chop onions very fine, add to mixture and mix well.
Chop meat.
Add 1 pkg. and 1/2 mixture and mix well.
Form mixture into a ball.
Roll cheese ball in remaining meat.
Refrigerate till ready to serve.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix vodka, whipping cream, lemon juice and powdered sugar in pitcher.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
To serve, pour 1 shot glass of this mixture over ice in a glass.
Add cream soda to fill. Garnish with a cinnamon stick or peppermint cane.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with eggs.
Stir in nuts and fruit. Add applesauce to which 1/2 teaspoon soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt have been added.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: lemon bread
directions: Beat together the shortening and 1 cup of the sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk to the sugar mixture, beating well after each addition.
Add nuts and lemon rind.
Turn batter into greased 8 1/2-inch bread pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Then add all of flour, 1 cup at a time.
Roll to 1/8-inch thickness and cut into shapes with cookie cutters.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef. Drain.
Add both cans of beans. In
large
bowl, add cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, onions and chilies.
Crumble up corn chips in same bowl.
When ready to serve,
pour
meat
and
bean mixture in bowl.
Pour salad dressing in.
Stir and serve.

title: chicken with lemon parsley sauce
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In small bowl, mix 1/3 cup soup and 1/4 cup milk.
Lightly coat chicken with flour.
Dip into soup mixture.
Coat with stuffing.
Place on baking sheet sprayed with Pam.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake 20 minutes or until no longer pink.
In small pan, mix remaining soup, 1/4 cup milk, lemon juice and parsley.
Over medium heat, heat thoroughly.
Serve with chicken.
This goes well with either rice or potatoes!
It's very good!

title: corned beef potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, pickles, onions and corned beef. Blend mayonnaise, mustard, chili sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour over potato mixture and toss lightly.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish, if desired, with crisp lettuce leaves, tomato wedges and carrot curls.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add strawberries, pineapple, lemon juice, bananas and nuts.
Put half of the mixture (2 to 2 1/2 cups) in an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator until congealed.
Pour sour cream over mixture in pan, then carefully spoon rest of the strawberry mixture over sour cream.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Spread bean dip in pan, then mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco sauce together and spread over bean dip.
Cup up green and black olives on top, then slice 1/2 green pepper, cut up tomato and then grated cheese all on top.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Cheese - Represents the moderation that Christians should practice in all things.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to cream mixture alternating with sour cream or buttermilk.
Blend in vanilla and nuts.
Chill until dough is firm.
Drop by spoonfuls on baking sheets about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400°.
Makes about 60 cookies.
Cool and ice.

title: melba's bread pudding
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; pour into a greased baking dish. Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Boil noodles and then cook hamburger. Mix all ingredients (except pepperoni and cheese) in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Set oven to 350° and bake for 45 minutes. Remove it from the oven and add pepperoni and cheese. Bake uncovered 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: barbecued redskins(serves 8)
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Add next 10 ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes and pour over frankfurters in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° (moderate oven) for 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Pour all canned vegetables in colander and drain.
Mix vegetables well.
Add celery, green pepper and onions.
Toss.

title: oriental chicken casserole
directions: Mix all and pour in baking dish.
Top with grated cheddar cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes until just done.
Peel and dice.
Snip bacon into 1/2-inch strips and fry until crisp.
While bacon is frying, saute onion with bacon.
Remove bacon and onion from skillet.
Stir in flour, sugar and salt into bacon drippings. Remove from heat and stir while adding vinegar mixed with water. Cook until mixture bubbles (about 2 minutes).
Add bacon, onion and potatoes; stir until all potatoes are coated.
Serve warm.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine ingredients.
Serve over ice.
Makes 14 servings of 6 ounces each.

title: sourdough hotcakes
directions: Mix wet ingredients in a bowl and dry ingredients in another bowl, then mix them together gradually, leaving a few lumps.
Fry on a moderately hot griddle.

title: egg nog
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Makes 4 cups mix.

title: chocolate walnut pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; add flour and sugars; mix until well blended.
Add butter; stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into a 9-inch deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour; serve warm with whipped cream.
If using a frozen pie shell, thaw completely; bake 10 minutes longer and place on cookie sheet. Recipe can be doubled.
Pie freezes very well.

title: caesar salad
directions: For dressing:
Put all ingredients into blender except oil. Blend very slowly; add oil until blended (gets thick and creamy). Makes 3/4 cup.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Arrange in layers potatoes, onion and cheese.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Dot with butter.
Cover with lid and bake 1 hour at 375°.
After 1 hour, remove cover and bake 15 minutes.
(Cook in 2-quart dish with cover.)

title: open faced mini reubens
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spread about 1/2 teaspoon dressing on each slice of bread; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Top each with slice of corned beef and about 1 tablespoon sauerkraut.
Cut cheese to fit bread; place over sauerkraut.
Bake for 10 minutes until cheese is melted.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: caesar salad
directions: Combine egg, lemon juice, anchovy paste, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and garlic oil in a container with a cover. Shake well.
Wash romaine; tear in small pieces.
Pour dressing over romaine and toss.
Add cheese, croutons and pepper to taste.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: In a bowl, cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add egg yolk and beat until mixture is smooth. Gradually add flour and mix until just blended. Turn into a shallow lightly greased 12 x 8 pan and spread evenly with back of spoon or spatula. Dip the tines of a fork in warm water. Make narrow ridges in the dough approximately 1/8-inch deep by marking lengthwise with tines of the fork. Repeat dipping and marking until entire surface is scored with lines. Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour or until golden brown. Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares while still hot. Let cool and remove from pan.

title: mexican cheese crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 250 degrees.
Place crackers in large shallow baking pan.
In a small bowl combine melted butter, taco seasoning, worcestershire sauce, and seasoned salt.
Pour mixture over crackers and stir well.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour onto wax paper to cool.
Store in an airtight container.
Yields 6 cups.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter in frypan; saute onion, celery and garlic until tender, but not brown. Add flour and seasonings; stir until blended. Stir in green pepper and tomatoes. Cook for 10 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally. Add shrimp; heat through.

title: gallehers meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato sauce and potatoes, carrot and onion chunks. Shape into meat loaf. Use a roasting pan with a lid. Place meat loaf in center of pan. Place potatoes, carrots and onion chunks around meat loaf. Pour tomato sauce over all. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake until carrots are done.

title: potatoes in tomato sauce
directions: Cook the potatoes and onion in butter for 20 minutes Add tomato juice, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
The potatoes thicken the tomato juice so that no other thickening is necessary.

title: spicy diet catsup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Simmer about 1 hour, until thick.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Partially cook broccoli.
Blend soup and flour; add sour cream, onion, salt and pepper. Layer sauce and broccoli in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine croutons with melted margarine. Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Mix all together in large pot. Stir continuously over low heat until it boils. (Will scorch easily.)
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring continuously off of bottom. Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Add vanilla.

title: no fuss standing rib roast
directions: Cut meat from bone; do not cut completely.
Press 1 clove garlic and spread between bone and meat.
Sprinkle with pepper seasoning.
Close meat; tie rib roast closed with butcher string. Sprinkle pepper and salt on outside of roast.
Sear the ends of roast in a hot pan.
Roast with bone up at 350°, approximately 20 minutes per pound.
Use meat thermometer until done.

title: golden potato doughnuts
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Beat eggs; add sugar, potatoes and bacon fat.
Beat well.
Add milk.
Combine but do not beat.
Add sifted dry ingredients and stir only until flour disappears.
Set in refrigerator to chill.
Divide dough.
Place 1/2 on floured cloth.
Pat out and sprinkle surface lightly with flour.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with doughnut cutter dipped in flour.
Fry in deep hot, 350°, fat until golden brown. While doughnuts are frying, roll out and cut the other part.
Roll in granulated or confectioners sugar.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: shrimp boat
directions: Crumble shrimp with fork.
Melt butter and add other ingredients except shrimp.
Mix unti smooth.
Add shrimp.
Take off heat.
Spread on muffins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into fourths.

title: toffee crunch cookies
directions: Beat shortening until creamy.
Add cake mix and water until blended.
Stir in brickle bits and nuts.
Drop dough by tablespoons on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are browned.
Top with look moist.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
