Mix remaining ingredients and stir well, so sugar is dissolved, then add salt and pepper to taste. Add to beans, etc.

title: orange surprise
directions: Mix Cool Whip and sour cream.
Add Jell-O powder and remaining ingredients, stirring gently.
Chill.

title: mushroom supreme
directions: Cut bacon into
pieces and cook.
Drain.
To 2 tablespoons of fat, add onions, mushrooms, cooked bacon pieces, salt and pepper and saute.
Add Worcestershire sauce and stir to mix.
Cover and keep warm until serving.
Serves 6.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off grease.
Add taco seasoning according to package directions.
Pour into dish and let cool.
Add sour cream over meat mixture, then spread refried beans over sour cream.
Melt Velveeta cheese in microwave with Ro-Tel.
Pour cheese and Ro-Tel over beans.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Cook on 300° for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mexican black-eyed peas
directions: Sort and wash peas.
Put in a large Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2-inches above peas.
Let soak overnight.
Brown sausage, stirring to crumble.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Drain. Drain peas well.
Stir in sausage and remaining ingredients. Bring to boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add water, if necessary.
Yields 10 servings.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sour cream, pepper and horseradish to taste.
Combine together.

title: vegetable rice
directions: Put butter in a 5-quart saucepan, at medium-high heat.
When melted, add all the spices.
Add the onion and saute until brown, then add the mixed vegetables and cook for 3 minutes.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend well.
Pour into a
greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cornbread tests done. Texture will be moist but firm enough to cut.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine all ingredients together. Spread into 13 x 9-inch pan prepared with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: milk gravy
directions: Use hot drippings from chicken or pork chops.
For each 3 tablespoons of drippings stir in 3 tablespoons of flour and blend well. Cook and stir until lightly browned.
Gradually add 1 1/2 to 2 cups hot milk. Cook and stir until thickened.

title: oven fried fish
directions: If frozen fish is used, thaw, rinse and dry.
Mix Rice Krispies, salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Pour margarine in shallow pan.
Dip fish in margarine and coat with crushed Rice Krispies.
Place in a single layer in well-greased, Pam sprayed, or foil-lined shallow pan.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Do not cover pan or turn fish while baking.
Serves 6.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift flour with other dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk, a little at a time, and yeast mixture to flour mixture.
Combine well, adding more buttermilk or flour as necessary, to make a soft, yet workable dough.
Knead gently for a few minutes on a floured board.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Brush with melted butter.
Place on lightly greased baking pan and bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Dough keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: peanut pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, syrup, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Add chopped peanuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Mix eggs at high speed gradually.
Add sugar until thick and lemony.
Pour corn oil into eggs and sugar.
Mix well.
Add alternately pumpkin and dry ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Bake in an ungreased angel food cake pan in a 350° oven for 70 to 75 minutes.
Cool completely before removing from pan.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in shrimp.
Saute for 1 minute. Add lemon juice and stir in flour.
Add cream, stirring until smooth.
Add salt, cloves and paprika and simmer gently for 5 minutes.
Beat eggs until light and stir in.
Add sherry just before serving.
Serve at once on toast or pastry shells.

title: lizzie's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and bourbon, mix well. Sift flour, soda and spices together several times.
Add fruit and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes.
Makes about 200 cookies.

title: angel fudge
directions: Place sugar, chocolate syrup and milk in a deep kettle (3-quart) and stir over medium heat until the ingredients are well blended.
Boil without stirring, until the mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat, add butter, vanilla and Marshmallow Creme.
Do not stir.
Cool undisturbed until the mixture has cooled to warm.
Beat vigorously until fudge loses gloss.
Pour into buttered pan, 8-inch square.
Cut into pieces.
Makes 3 dozen pieces.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken and break meat into pieces, saving broth.
Melt margarine and stir into dressing and seasoning packets.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Saute vegetables in 1/2 cup oil.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, water, salt, Red Devil sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer for at least 45 minutes, covered. Put in shrimp and cook until done, about 7 to 10 minutes.
Then add cooked rice.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, egg and molasses.
Blend in remaining ingredients except granulated sugar.
Cover; chill overnight.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Dip tops in granulated sugar.
Place balls sugar side up.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Fold in flavoring by hand.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 325°.
Start cake in a cold oven.
Don't open the door while cooking.

title: hot and sassy oyster crackers
directions: Excluding crackers, mix all ingredients in a pan and heat just long enough for oil to get warm, not hot.
Don't boil.
Stir in crackers and toss until coated.
Let cool and store in an airtight container.
Chex cereals are great mixed with these crackers.

title: caramel corn
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, heat sugar, salt, syrup and butter on low/medium until melted.
Bring to boil; let bubble for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add baking soda.
Stir.
(Sauce gets fluffy and lighter.)
Pour over popcorn on ungreased cookie sheet and coat well.
Put in warm oven.
Stir every 15 minutes for 1 hour. Cool on wax paper.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Place chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Marinate 1 hour. Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 45 minutes more, until tender.

title: macaroon and chocolate pudding(very rich)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 tablespoons cold water. Add 1/4 cup boiling water.
When cool, add it to the whipped cream (stiff). Divide cream into 2 portions.
Add melted chocolate to 1 portion and macaroons to the other.
In a pan (I use spring-form pan), layer 1/2 of the white and layer chocolate, then white or as you wish, in layers.
Remove the outside of the spring-form pan.

title: autumn cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine stuffing with melted butter.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook chicken until tender and remove from bone.
Place shredded chicken over stuffing.
Mix soup and broth together and pour over chicken.
Put remaining stuffing over chicken and bake for 30 minutes at 350° until the crust is lightly browned.

title: picadillo(a cuban recipe for ground meat; latin-american dish)
directions: Brown the meat in skillet and set aside, draining off excess fat.
Heat the oil in a heavy saucepan.
Add onion and cook until onion is soft and golden.
Add all ingredients, except ground meat, green pepper and raisins.
Stir, lower heat, cover saucepan and simmer for at least 20 minutes.
Stir frequently, returning cover to pan after each stirring.
Add the meat, raisins and green pepper, but if you like crisp pepper, add it just before serving. Cook for another 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Servings 8 to 10.

title: veal with lemon strips
directions: Take the lemon peel and cut it into paper thin strips, about 2 tablespoons.
Heat oil and quickly saute the veal.
Keep veal warm.
Drain oil.
Add lemon strips and remaining ingredients and boil until it becomes slightly thick.
Pour over veal.

title: herb blend
directions: Place all ingredients in a small jar and seal.
Shake until mixture is completely blended.
Yields 3/4 cup of seasoning.

title: mustard glaze
directions: Combine ingredients.
Brush mixture on ham frequently during the last hour of baking.
Makes 1 cup (enough for 10 to 13 pound ham).
Also good on roast chicken and turkey or as a dipping sauce for shrimp or chicken nuggets.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in baking dish in the oven. Mix Bisquick, salt, pepper and paprika in a bowl.
Coat all sides of chicken with mixture.
Put in baking dish, skin side down. Bake for 40 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake for 15 more minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Mix cake, dry pudding and seed.
Add water and oil; beat in eggs one at a time.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add celery, carrots, potatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer until tender.
Add creamed corn and milk. Heat and serve.

title: party potatoes
directions: Prepare instant potatoes as per package directions.
Add the next 4 ingredients to potatoes.
Blend until well mixed.
Pour into large casserole.
Drizzle with melted oleo.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 12.

title: lime sweet pickles
directions: Wash and cut up cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Stir as often as you can with wooden spoon.
After 24 hours, wash lime mix off 3 to 4 times to make sure the lime mixture is off.
Put on a towel to drain and let all the water drain off.
Mix and bring to a boil the sugar, pickling spices and vinegar and let it be syrupy.
Drop cucumbers in and let set for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, not over 4 hours. Bring to a boil and boil for 30 minutes.
Can and seal.

title: peanut butter banana sandwiches
directions: Toast the bread in toaster.
Spread one side of two slices with some peanut butter.
Peel banana.
Cut banana in half crosswise and again lengthwise to make 4 pieces.
Put 2 pieces of banana on one slice of the peanut butter toast.
Top with a plain slice of toast.
Repeat with remaining banana and toast.
Cut each sandwich in half.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Mix margarine and eggs together and add to flour and sugar mixture.
Press on floured board until firm; make small balls and press with fork on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until brown.

title: ginger ale mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add salt; cool.
Add ginger ale.
Chill until partially set.
Add rest of ingredients to the gelatin mixture.
Pour in a mold.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef, green pepper and onions.
Drain excess grease. Add chili sauce and soup.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: fruit, nut and rice casserole
directions: Cover fruit with water and soak for 1 hour.
Cook rice according to directions.
In skillet, melt butter.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Add curry.
Add toasted almonds, drained fruit and rice.
Put into greased baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa in the top of a double boiler. Add small amount of milk (which has been scalded).
Beat egg yolks into this mixture; slowly add the rest of the milk.
Cool slowly.

title: steak parmesan
directions: Beat together egg, water and pepper. Combine crumbs and 1/2 cup of cheese. Dip steak in egg mixture, then crumbs.
Brown steaks in hot oil.
Drain on paper towels.
Arrange steak in pan. Cover with pizza sauce and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Yields 5 servings.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomatoes.
Fill tomatoes.
Serve on lettuce with wedges of cheese.

title: oklahoma oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and butter; add eggs and beat until creamy.
Mix next 8 ingredients and add to creamy mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Form cookies into small golf ball size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and mash slightly with fork.
Bake in 325° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fudge marble bars
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside cocoa packet. Combine cake mix, 1/4 cup water, eggs and butter in large bowl.
Beat at low speed with mixer; just until blended. Measure 1/2 cup batter in small bowl.
Add cocoa packets, chocolate chips and 1 tablespoon water, stir until blended.
Add nuts to yellow batter, spread in pan, spoon chocolate batter randomly on top and swirl with a knife.
Bake for 22 to 27 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Wash corned beef in cold water to remove the brine.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Pour in strawberries, eggs and oil.
Mix by hand.
Add food coloring.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Partially cook potatoes in boiling water; cool and peel.
Slice 1/4-inch thick lengthwise.
Put in a baking dish in layers.
Boil water and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are clear and syrup is thick.

title: mincemeat jello
directions: Dissolve cherry jello in hot water; pour a layer in a 9 x 12-inch pan or 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Chill remaining jello until firm in another pan or mold.
Add rest of ingredients on top.
When second pan is firm, serve upside down on clear layer and top with sweet cream.

title: chicken pie
directions: Precook chicken; place chopped meat in a casserole dish.
Mix chicken broth and soup; pour over chicken.
Combine plain flour, baking powder, milk, salt and oleo.
Pour over the chicken and broth mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: jellied beet salad mold
directions: Drain beets. Add water to make 1 cup. Bring to a boil, remove from heat and stir in jello until dissolved. Add rest of ingredients and put into mold. Refrigerate.

title: light and easy cheesecake
directions: Layer ladyfingers on bottom and around sides of spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese and Cool Whip until smooth.
Add 2 packages of cheesecake mix.
Mix in milk and vanilla until well blended.
Pour into spring-form pan.
Chill overnight, if possible, if not several hours.
Remove from pan.
Garnish with fruit, if desired.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Put all crackers in Ziploc bag.
Mix all other ingredients very well in a bowl.
Pour into bag of crackers.
Shake well.
Lay bag of crackers down to marinate for approximately 2 hours.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken in 4-quart pan.
Remove chicken when done and leave just enough water to cook spaghetti.
Cook spaghetti and let broth boil down.
While noodles are cooking, in another 4-quart pan, melt butter.
Add bell pepper, onion, mushrooms and olives and saute.
Add Ro-Tel and mushroom soup to mixture.
Stir to blend.
Cut Velveeta into chunks; add to mixture.
Grate Cheddar cheese and add 2/3 of cheese to
mixture.
Cook on low heat until cheese is melted.
Combine noodles, chicken and cheese sauce.
Put in a large ovenproof dish.
Add remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cheese melts and meal bubbles.
This makes a lot!
Can be frozen.

title: baked potato soup
directions: In al large kettle melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Heat and stir until smooth.
Add milk, stirring until thickened.
Add potatoes and onions.
Bring just to a boil;
reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes;
stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients.
stir until cheese is melted.
Served hot.

title: cherry bars
directions: Bring to a full boil then pour on the last 3 ingredients and mix.
Press into a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan and chill.

title: fruit pie
directions: Layer bottom of dish with graham crackers.
Mix condensed milk and fruit.
Layer over crackers.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Chill for about an hour and serve.

title: onion pie
directions: Saute onions in margarine over medium heat until tender, but not brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.
In bowl, beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Spread onions in pie shell; add Cheddar cheese evenly over top.
Pour egg mixture over all and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 minutes.
Lower oven to 300° and bake 15 minutes more or until inserted knife blade is clean.
Let cool before serving.

title: desha's cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Pour into well-greased pan. Use a 9 x 12-inch pan or a small loaf pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve with honey butter.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix well to make a textured finger paint.
Add tempera paint to the water to provide coloring.

title: chicken pie
directions: Break up chicken and place
in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix broth and chicken soup until smooth and pour over chicken. Salt and pepper.
Mix
flour, buttermilk and margarine, making a batter.
Pour over chicken and bake at
400° for 30 minutes. To brown crust, broil until lightly brown (1 can of Veg-All or frozen vegetables may be added).

title: cherry delight
directions: Prepare like pie crust (no liquids).
Line bottom of cake pan and halfway up the sides with crust.
Press with fingers.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: squash appetizer
directions: Peel and chop squash.
Cook without adding water over low heat with onion, green pepper and coriander (or parsley).
Add cut sausage (or ground beef), stir well.
Season with salt and pepper and cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Serve hot on "tortillas."

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: *You will use these items to dip balls in before cooking.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and syrup.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter in frypan; saute onion.
Add mushrooms with liquid and soup.
Stir until smooth.
Add chicken, evaporated milk, marjoram, salt, Cheddar cheese and celery salt.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat. Add pizza sauce, seasoning, and milk. Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Add mushrooms, layer meat mixture and rotini in 2 quart casserole. Cover with cheese. Bake covered at 350 degrees. for 25-30 minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Mix well and pour onto hot waffle iron.

title: bobbie and dawn's "vegetable pack supper"
directions: Take a 9 x 13-inch pan and line with foil leaving about a foot of foil hanging off each side of the pan.
Lay your meat in the bottom of the pan.
Spice as you normally would.
Add your veggies, spices, butter and pour water over the top.
Seal the foil up good so the steam does not escape.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cut raw bacon into small pieces.
Add onion and green pepper and fry together until bacon is cooked.
Do not drain bacon grease.
Grind the frozen corn in a blender until small pieces. Add to bacon, onion and green pepper mixture.
Add water and cook slowly until corn is cooked.
This will be quite thick and burns easily, so watch it carefully.
You can add more water if necessary.
Add flour mixed with small amount of water.
Stir. Add milk and half and half and heat slowly (don't boil).
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: potato casserole(serves 12 people)
directions: Defrost hash brown potatoes; mix with all other ingredients except 1/2 stick butter and corn flakes.
Put into a large 9 x 12-inch baking pan or dish.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter with the corn flakes and spread on top of mixture.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and put into a casserole dish.

title: brown sugar drops
directions: Mix brown sugar, shortening, water and egg. Stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: cheese squares
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar; add flour and nuts.
Mix to crumb mixture.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased baking dish.

title: creamed ham
directions: Melt butter in saucepan or skillet.
Blend in flour and salt. Let bubble together.
Take off heat.
Add milk all at once.
Cook over low to medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add ham, peas, pepper and salt to taste.
Cook until meat and peas are hot.
For thinner sauce, add more milk.
For thicker sauce, use less milk.
Serve over toast.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix in a heavy skillet the Karo syrup and sugar; heat.
Add 2 cups raw peanuts and cook until light beige in color.
Add the paraffin and remove from heat; stir in baking soda.
Do this fast as it will foam and need to be put on a greased cookie sheet and spread thin before it hardens.
Cool and break into small pieces. Store in airtight container.

title: chicken with wine casserole
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Combine next 5 ingredients.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour mixture over chicken and then top with the almonds.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Serves 4.

title: easy casserole
directions: Cook meat until done.
In a baking dish with cover, layer meat, potatoes, carrots and onions, then repeat until meat and vegetables are used up.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice to a boil.
Take off of stove and add apricot jello.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Cool in refrigerator until completely cold, but not set.
Add the 2 cups of buttermilk to Cool Whip.
Add chopped pecan nuts as desired. Chill overnight.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: escalloped eggplant(1964 cookbook)
directions: Peel and
cut eggplant in 1-inch cubes; cook in boiling water 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into buttered 1 quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed for 20 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let cool and add glaze.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in dish.
Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.

title: almond sticks
directions: Mix all ingredients to form dough.
For easier handling, place dough in refrigerator 2 hours before rolling on.
Place dough on floured board.
Divide into 8 equal sections.
Roll each section to about 15 x 4-inch.

title: mom's angel food pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water in top of double boiler.
Cook for 12 minutes or until thick and clear.
Add salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff with sugar.
Pour cornstarch mixture in and heat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell. Let cool.
Serve topped with whipped cream and shaved chocolate.

title: butter ball cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Beat until light.
Add vanilla, flour and eggs.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: no-fat hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Stir in nuts (optional).
Spread mixture in a 9-inch square pan, sprayed with nonstick spray.
Sprinkle mixture with brown sugar and cocoa mixed together.
Pour water over mixture!
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
To serve, cut into squares and invert onto dish.
Top with fat-free ice cream or frozen yogurt.
Spoon remaining sauce over ice cream.

title: kathy's cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Cut cheese in cubes.
Put all ingredients in a bowl and microwave on Medium-high until cheese is a smooth consistency, stirring often.

title: dill pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers lengthwise or into chunks.
Combine garlic, salt, vinegar and water; heat to boiling.
Remove garlic and place 4 pieces in each jar along with 4 sprigs dill and 4 peppercorns. Pour hot vinegar solution on top of cucumbers in jars.
Leave 1-inch headspace.
Put alum on top of cucumbers and seal jars. Process 10 minutes as soon as you put in canner.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken into egg and then into bread crumbs.
Heat olive oil.
Cook chicken in oil until done and well browned.
Pour sauce into 11 x 7-inch dish.
Place chicken on sauce, top with cheeses.
Bake about 25 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cook bacon and drain.
Break lettuce and cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients.
In a bowl, layer lettuce, cauliflower, crumbled bacon and dressing.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours (overnight is fine).
Mix together just before serving.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Combine dry pudding mix, milk, cream cheese and whipped topping.
Place 1/3 of the cookie crumbs in bottom of a serving dish.
Next, put a layer of the pudding mixture.
Repeat layers, topping with crumbs.
Chill.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: mushrooms parmesan
directions: Clean the mushrooms and remove stems.
Place caps, open end up, in a shallow greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Set aside. Finely chop the mushroom stems.
Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a skillet.
Add mushroom stems, onion and garlic.
Cook slowly until onion and garlic are slightly browned. Combine bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt and oregano.
Mix in the onion, garlic and mushroom stems.
Lightly fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Pour 2 tablespoons olive oil into the baking dish. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until mushrooms are tender and tops are browned.

title: company pickle chunks(these are sweet, crisp and clear)
directions: Cover cucumbers with boiling water.
Let stand until next morning.
Drain.
Repeat this procedure the next 3 mornings.
On the fifth day, drain and slice in 1/2-inch wedges.

title: north shore potatoes
directions: Store cooked potatoes in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Melt butter with cheese in double boiler.
Add sour cream, salt, pepper and onion; stir until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Peel potatoes; grate them and stir into cheese mixture.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: christmas stolen
directions: In a large bowl, mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast. Combine milk, water and margarine in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat until warm (margarine doesn't need to melt).
Gradually add liquids to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed and 2 minutes on high speed.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough. Turn onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: butter pecan bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter, this makes crust.
Place in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cream remaining 3 ingredients.
Spread on crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cook and cut into bars.

title: mrs. linda's italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco, sugar and egg yolks.
Add flour and soda. Add buttermilk.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into mixture. Stir in coconut and pecans.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans, rounds pans for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time to creamed mixture.
Add flour, one cup at a time to creamed mixture, alternating 7-Up and adding the last of flour. Add in vanilla extract.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Chop celery, pepper and onion.
Mix all ingredients.
Marinate in 1/4 cup wine vinegar and 1/2 cup oil.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: coffee coogan
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Cover generously with sugar.
Top with ground cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
After the first 15 minutes, dribble 2 tablespoons melted butter over top.
Return to oven for remaining 15 minutes.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: Mix Cream of Wheat with substitute eggs.
Mix all remaining ingredients in second bowl.
Add egg mixture.
Spray a loaf pan or 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chewy cheesecake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and oleo with hands; press into 8 x 11-inch pan.
Cover with chopped pecans.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: curry dip
directions: Combine and mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli, onions and eggs.
Mix in mushrooms and mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add ingredients in order given.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let cool before cutting in squares.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix and put in 1 gallon ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Blend well. Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with fruit, if desired.
You can make ahead and freeze.
Take out 1 hour before using.

title: coleslaw
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage. Add salt and knead well.
Add other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and boil until thick.
Cool overnight.
In a baked pie crust, put strawberries (can use bananas).
Pour Jell-O mix over berries and chill.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Add salt and pepper to beef and onion and brown in greased skillet, then add other ingredients and stuff in green peppers. Put in pan with a little water and cook in oven with low heat until peppers are tender.

title: ooey gooey bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 stick melted butter and 2 eggs and pour into a flat Pyrex dish or aluminum pan that has been greased and floured. Mix the xxx sugar, cream cheese and 1 stick melted butter, then spread this mixture over the first layer in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well. Stir in peanut butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Form into tiny balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with back of a fork to make crisscross.
Dough may also be rolled and cut, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: cheese cake
directions: Use spring-form pan.
Grease bottom and sides of pan.
Combine crumbs, sugar and butter and press in bottom of pan.
Mix first 4 ingredients until fluffy.
Pour in on crust.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: blueberries 'n cheese coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Combine 2 cups flour, salt and baking soda; add to batter alternately with the milk and water.
Coat the blueberries with the 1/4 cup flour; fold into batter gently with cream cheese and rind.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
(I just spray the glass pan with Pam.
Glass pans seem to work better than metal.)
Top with topping.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and chill overnight.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine in a saucepan.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: blueberry cafluti
directions: Mix together the eggs, sugar, flour, margarine and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Spread the cracker crumbs on bottom of pie shell.
Place the blueberries (drained) in pie shell.
Pour mixture over berries.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
Top with whipped topping or Cool Whip.
Serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: ranch pinwheels
directions: Mix together the Ranch dressing, onions and cream cheese and spread evenly on tortillas.
Roll in four tight rolls and wrap in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate overnight or freeze.
Cut off edges if ragged.
Slice into pinwheels.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Fry and crumble sausage; drain.
Combine with all ingredients except shredded cheese.
Wash and remove stems from mushrooms.

title: dried pea sausage
directions: Cook peas until they are soft; mash peas.
Mix mashed peas with salt and pepper, sage, red pepper, egg and milk (use milk if the mixture is dry).
Add flour to mixture and form patties.
Fry in about three tablespoons of oil or lard, browning on both sides.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Line a baking sheet with wax paper.
In a medium size bowl, mix peanut butter, margarine, vanilla and sugar with hands to form a smooth dough.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Shape dough into balls, using 2 teaspoons for each.
Place on wax paper and put in refrigerator.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix eggs and water together.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Spray pan with Pam.

title: tasti-little b's
directions: Brown round and sausage until well cooked.
Drain meat on paper toweling and put back into frying pan.
Add all seasonings and blend well.
Add shredded cheese and warm until all cheese has melted.
Remove from heat and place approximately 1 tablespoon meat mixture onto each party rye slice.
Place each party rye slice onto cookie sheet and broil until hot and bubbly.
Serve immediately. (These appetizers will freeze up nicely for approximately 2 to 3 weeks before broiling.)

title: nacho dip
directions: Fry meats; drain.
Melt cheese over low heat, stirring often. Add salsa and meat. Serve with nacho chips.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place cubed bread in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Blend in all remaining ingredients.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
(This would have been placed 1-inch from the edge of the baking dish.)
Bub's Lemon Sauce is a great topping for bread pudding.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Grease a large 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Press crust over bottom.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown (15 minutes).
Don't refrigerate.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, melted margarine and pecans together.
Press into long baking dish (9 x 13-inch) and bake 25 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Press 3/4 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch container and freeze. Soften 1/2 gallon vanilla ice cream and spread over frozen crust. Freeze again.
Pour 1 large can chocolate syrup on ice cream. Sprinkle remaining Rice Chex mix on top and freeze.
Take out 10 minutes before serving.

title: calamati con ponodoro
directions: Have squid thoroughly cleaned.
Cut into small pieces; wash well.
Pour olive oil in saucepan and heat; brown garlic about 3 minutes.
Add squid; cover and saute 10 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, oregano and sherry; cook 10 minutes longer over low flame. Add tomatoes and parsley; cover and cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken-cheese rolls
directions: Place split breasts between waxed paper; pound to 1/2-inch thickness. Spread each with about 3 tablespoons cheese mixture; dot with 1/2 teaspoon butter.
Fold ends over filling (some will ooze out during baking).
Wrap 1 slice bacon around each roll. Place, seam side down, in shallow baking pan.
Bake on top rack in 400° oven for 40 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear when meat is pierced.
Broil about 5 minutes or until bacon is crisp and golden.
Serves 6.

title: baked lasagne
directions: *Ricotta
cheese
(equal amount) may be substituted for cottage cheese.

title: chocolate fondue(yields 2 cups)
directions: Put all ingredients, except fruit, in fondue saucepan directly over flame and stir until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Partially cover flame so that mixture is just kept warm. Spear pieces of fruit with fondue forks or long picks and dip into melted chocolate.
Swirl to remove excess chocolate.

title: sugar-free pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients into bowl.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Provides 1 bread, 2 fats, 3 extra, 1/4 egg, 2 teaspoons vegetable and 2/3 calorie.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in large shallow dish in given order.
Use dressing on top.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Place oil in frying pan over medium heat.
Add chopped onion, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook until onion is tender. Add tomato paste and water.
Meanwhile, place the can of tomato sauce in a large pan along with water and sugar.
When mixture in frying pan is blended together and simmering, it is time to pour it into the large saucepan with tomato sauce and sugar.
Stir altogether and simmer on low.
Add meat balls.

title: chocolate banana cream pie
directions: Arrange banana slices on bottom of crust; set aside.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits as directed.
Add egg, cheese, pepper and butter. Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy one-dish supper
directions: Brown beef and onions in a Dutch oven.
Add onions, mushrooms, tomato sauce or tomatoes, catsup, oregano, thyme, basil, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cool to warm. Divide dough into 20 pieces and place on top of warm beef mixture. Cover; let rise 30 minutes or until pieces of bread dough have doubled in size.
Lightly brush dough with beaten egg.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot chocolate(microwave)
directions: Combine chocolate, water, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg in a bowl.
Cook, uncovered, 4 minutes, stirring every 1 minute.
Add milk and cook another 6 minutes.
Add marshmallows and almond extract.
Whisk until frothy.
Cook 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: freezer bread sticks(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Add margarine. Add water to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Add 1/2 cup flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in more flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a well floured board. Divide dough into 16 pieces.
Roll each into an eighteen-inch rope. Cut each rope into three 6-inch ropes.
Place on greased baking sheet, rolling to grease all sides of dough.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Freeze until firm.
Transfer to plastic bags.
Freeze up to 4 weeks.
Remove from freezer; place on ungreased baking sheet. Cover.
Let stand at room temperature until thawed, about 30 minutes.
Let rise until doubled, about 15 minutes.
Brush with combined egg white and cold water; sprinkle with seed.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry almond bread
directions: Combine egg, milk, butter and almond extract.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add to liquid ingredients mixing until moist.
Fold in cranberries.
Spread batter in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and almonds (press into batter slightly).
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Turn down oven to 350° and bake for 30 more minutes.
